76561197968514473,Recommended,268500,20996631,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Meat-King©®,"""Never was so much owed by so many to so few. This was their finest hour.""XCOM 2 is a turn-based strategy game developed by the company Firaxis Games with emphasis on tactical combat.Atmosphere & presentation:+ The game captures the feel of a resistance force opposing an overwhelming alien occupation.+ Excellent soundtrack that keeps the player in the game and sets the mood.+ Detail put into level design and environmental effects is impressive.+ Some fighting mechanics are cinematic, intuitive and entertaining.+ It boasts a healthy variety of equipment, firearms and peripherals.+ Partially destructible environments.+ Interface is minimalist and aesthetically pleasing.+ Offers very high replayability.o Game is not optimized for 4K resolution, causing irregular fps drops.- Quite a few bugs and glitches, ranging from minor clipping issues to enemies shooting through obstacles / walls. [Thanks to Volvox Globator for highlighting these points.]- Occasional in-game slowdowns during certain events, e.g. pause between rounds, calculation of burning effects etc.Combat & gameplay:+ The game encourages the player to recruit and build a highly specialised army, and the mechanics put in place for doing so are well-rounded and sophisticated.+ Alien AI behaviour is mostly unpredictable, therefore adding to the title's challenge and replayability.+ Some missions offer a stealth system, allowing the player to scout out the land and enemies before engaging.+ Reliable cover system and shooting mechanics, supporting offensive and defensive approaches.+ Positioning and taking advantage of terrain are the keys to success.+ Base building and economics add another layer of challenge to the game.+ Broad spectrum of weapon customizations enriches the gameplay.+ For the masochistic hardcore gamers among us, the legendary ‘Ironman’ mode is available.o Learning curve is initially a bit steep, and may deter more casual gamers. In comparison with its predecessor the general level of difficulty is higher.o Missions are rng-based (random number generator), which could result in a lot of timed missions or almost no timed missions. [Thanks to Athena for mentioning this point.]Characters & story:+ Campaign playthrough is engaging and provides diversified side quests, with different mission goals and winning conditions.+ The narrative is well-delivered, with an even pace and solid character development.+ Extensive customization options for the characters and the possibility to export and import the party setup.+ The player is likely to develop emotional attachment to some of the soldiers, increasing the immersion into the game.o Solid voice acting of the entire cast.Summary:XCOM 2 offers a superb strategy experience, which manages to improve the original XCOM formula on every level.Achievements:Estimated time for 100% completion: +100 hoursSingleplayer achievements: 79Multiplayer achievements: 1"
