76561198038048005,Not Recommended,268500,28585834,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,DeValiere,"Updated Review (11 JAN 2017):NOTE: To be clear, the majority of my gameplay time on this game falls between initial release and the last patch, when I encountered no problems other than mod conflicts. As with most of my Steam games, I didn't bother with a review. Plenty of others were raving about the game so why should I say the same things? Lazy? Yeah.That said I'm going to start this update by clearly stating that XCOM2 is one of my favourite games EVER. Its not the kind of game to give up on easily. Even though I was pretty angry when the last patch broke my install, and posted my initial review (below) as a result, I just couldn't let it go. It may be worth noting I didn't discover this right away as I'd been neck deep in other games prior to and after the patch. Stupid Orcs. Found out when game tanked while I was showing it off to a mate. Murphy's Law I guess.This update is posted about a week into my latest clean install. And by clean, this time I mean both the Steam folder and the OS drive ""My Games"" folder - only my character pool was spared the axe. I then verified my game cache via Steam, and once the entire 29gb reinstall was done, I used steam to create a desktop icon.As of right now, still getting red screen error on launch, but a simple tweak of launch options made that go away - seems to be for a multiplayer file or some such, so don't care. Tweaked graphics settings and then ran game. So far, it's running moderately well, but still a few crashes. Having sifted through several very long forum posts (one of which was 30 pages long) trying to get a handle on what causes the crashes I pretty much gave up. There seem to be multiple possibilities. Still, frustrating.So... where does that leave this review? Hmmm... Well, I'm still leaving it as a thumbs down for the simple reason that I really prefer not to have to stuff around this much to get a great game running again after a patch. Nor can I ignore the fact it's still crashing sporadically for me. My comments re optimisation still stand. Frame rate is all over the place. It is just my opinion but I feel that a game this good should be able to reach as many players as possible - not everyone has a high end PC so a little more work to iron out performance on mid / upper-mid range machines would be in everyone's best interest. I cannot review this any other way as this is my experience and also that of others.HOWEVER!!!! It would be unfair not to also add that this game is pretty frickin' awesome when it runs without crashing. The level of customisation of your characters is a 10/10 as are many  aspects of tactical gameplay. It is not an easy game to master, but rewarding as you slowly learn how to. Odds can feel like they're stacked against you and at times they are. Your grunts are going to miss a 90% shot chance on an enemy standing a tile away - that I think is a little overboard but your memorial wall is fairly large so... yeah. Enemy numbers and stats level with you - well, they can out-level you at times in fact - so you're never really going to rest easy. And just when you think things can’t get worse... they will.Also not a huge fan of the timed missions (not all are timed however), mostly because I'm a turtle at heart and like to take my time - rushing to beat a timer detracts from the tactical aspect of the game for me. To a degree, this also holds true for the campaign map - there is a definite gearing towards pushing you ever onwards - a game design decision some will like and some will not. It certainly ramps up the tension and fits with the narrative. This is personal choice IMO, and as I say, I'm a slow poke. I don't see this aspect of the game as a negative as such, but perhaps an option to extend play time might be an idea. Oh, for days gone by and the Longwar mod...Without Longwar Studios Toolbox, or another mod, your camera angles are only adjustable by 90 degrees - one of the few things I really didn't like control wise. There can also be some quirks with moving characters - one wrong click and a grunt can be toast. Not a game breaker, just need to be super careful.Mod support is good but you do need to be careful as mod conflicts can cause issues and I found (regretfully) that the ""more map"" style mods may cause problems so I haven't used any of those in some time just to be safe. IMO, there are some mods that are must haves but I'd recommend playing vanilla at least once to get a feel for what you might want to tweak or improve. I'd also note here that if you're using certain combinations of mods, and with the way the XComEngine.ini file works, you may need to delete it (easier than editing) before starting the game to purge mod overwrite data - especially if you're using Longwar Toolbox in combination with certain other mods. Meh.Conclusion: Great game with a few optimisation issues IMO - enough to keep it from a thumbs up. On sale, it is definitely worth buying. I pre-ordered my copy BTW - and ultimately I don't regret it but am frustrated with it at times. Could just do without the crashes. Can live with the rest. Despite issues, I'm not going to stop playing the game. That might not make sense to some people, but that's the way it is. I just can't give a thumbs up in it's current state.TL:DR ...* Gameplay / Features: 7/10* Mods / Steam Workshop: 9/10* Optimisation / Performance: 6/10 (on an pretty good but not super-beast PC); needswork in that regard IMO* Stability: 5/10 (harrumph!)* Replayability / Map variety:  7/10 (map layout, while procedurally generated, doesfeel limited and over time, repetitive).* DLC: 5/10 - OK with what there is, but would like to see more content please* Overall: 7/10 (pretty much excluding crashing issues)Have a nice day...===============================================================Original Review:As you can see by the hours I've put into this game, it's one of my favourites. However, at this time I feel compelled to write a review, and it is going to be a negative one. Why? Because of the following:* Poor optimisation: I can run this OK with a few tweaks to graphics settings, but it feels as if the devs could do some more work on this.* As of late DEC 2016, cannot play without continual crashes and freezes -  a problem that was common at game release and then seemed to be fixed by devs before making a big comeback with latest patch. Game has become most temperamental and frankly I'm over spending time trying to ""fix"" the problems.Therefore, I couldn't recommend purchase at this time - essentially playing russian roulete as to whether the game will run OK for you or not - regardless of whether you run a clean install or modded. Don't be fooled by devs blaming mods for instability and crashes."
