,Not Recommended,268500,21213140,"Posted: 14 February, 2016",all,Kiwi,"Jeez, I really like XCOM, however, at the moment it is difficult to recommend.In a lot of ways this sequel is a move in the right direction. The game makes you feel pressured and you often have to decide on the best of two bad options. The field game is a lot more in depth and plays a lot more like old school X-Com. that said there are a lot of problems. Some of this stuff can be fixed with patches, however, on some level the game is just fundamentally flawed.It's hard, and I'm fine with that, XCOM should be hard, though I feel a lot of the time it's hard in the wrong ways.The missions often have time limits, and that's okay in itself but combine that with the way aliens enter the fight (they become active in packs of 2-3 as soon as one of your soldiers spots one of the pack, at which point they get a free move to cover) means that it is never smart to push out more than a few spaces a turn. If you discover a pack with your penultimate or last move of a round, 2-3 strong aliens get a free move to cover (or, even worse flank you) and then have a whole round to take down a couple of guys.The game pushes you forward with time limits and then punishes you for moving forward at even a moderate rate.Also, a lot of people seem to feel melee is OP, I'm not sure I'd agree with that, but I don't think it feels very good. If you run up and take a sword swipe at something and miss, that soldier is probably dead.The geoscape gameplay is not very well explained either, I'd advise treating your first game as a throwaway until you get the hang of how that works.Lastly, this game is really badly optimised, lots and lots of slowdowns, the game hanging for 5-10 seconds. Lots of gaps in the action, you'll throw a grenade, and there is significant gaps between the grenade being thrown, exploding, damage being dealt and the next action taking place.This game does have a lot of potential, but I don't think they can change the gameplay enough with patches to really make the gameplay coherent, the mechanics complementary and the difficulty.tough but fair."
