,Not Recommended,268500,32976466,Posted: 28 June,all,wc901107,"Despite that this game has a good story background and rich game elements, it has fatal problems that not worth to waste your money.1. Buggy & poor performance- The game crashes quite often, and sometimes just stuck on loading.- Keyboard disorders sometimes and- The game consumers a lot of resources when the graphic is just not that good.2. Bad UXThe UX design is a pain point of this game. The buttons/options/widgets are just not very responsive. You may very easily misclick or select on wrong option. Then the whole battle is ruined, and you have to reload or suck it. For first few play through, you just don’t know how some researches/items work, unless you search online. You pay extra time to figure out something that they suppose to tell you in the game.3. Ridiculous battle systemSeriously, the designer must really hate people. The battle system is not just hard, but makes no sense.The whole RNG design is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t. For Civilization 4, the battle RNG is okay. Because you can product a large enough army, so one bad luck consequence is minimized. Rr you can avoid war to avoid rolling the dice. But in this game, the battle scale is so small, one bad luck may determine whether you win the battle, or fail the mission and your whole elites get wiped out. A game can be hard, but it has to be hard for a reason. You can punish players for their bad choices but not their bad luck.Many settings are just anti common sense. Like enemies get a cover bonus, even if the cover is not even in the way. At the moment you release it, you find out you stand on front of enemy, can’t cancel,  hit, miss and get killed in next turn. Then again, you have to search online to see what exact the cover condition is and try to memorize it.The way enemies engaging the battle is also ridiculous. After lose your concealment, There is no way you can predict the when to engage the enemies and yet it is the most important part in the battle. It is very likely you get engage battle with two group of enemies at same time for no reason and just lose your best soldiers. Again, luck plays an important role here, which makes the game experience even worse.A game can be hard, but shouldn’t be hard like this way. A game can have RNG, but shouldn’t punishing players hard for their bad lucks.If you really like this type of game, go to play super robot wars series, which have much more friendly design."
