76561198040259135,Recommended,268500,23499882,"Posted: 11 June, 2016",all,Premeditated Chaos,"A worthy successor to the XCOM franchise, featuring your usual incompetent rookies with crappy off-the-shelf gear, RNG that'll make you wish you weren't playing on Ironman mode, and a wide variety of aliens ready to perpetrate all of the usual♥♥♥♥♥♥moves upon your soldiers. Like its predecessors, this game is NOT a power fantasy and will constantly remind you of that.If you're looking for a challenging turn-based strategy game with a campaign polished to perfection and a plethora of replayability as you work your way up the difficulties (and take off the training wheels by turning on Ironman mode), look no further. Just the base game was worth every penny, though I can't speak for the DLC or mods.But before you buy, some cons worth noting: this game has a few performance issues and bugs, though most of them have been patched out over time. If you don't want to play with ""potato"" graphics, you'll need a good-quality computer.Also, there is a multiplayer, but it's very barebones with a ranked leaderboard and not much else, though there are still people playing and the netcode/balance is adequate."
76561198008405446,Recommended,268500,29307098,Posted: 16 January,all,Armoured Centurion,"XCOM 2 is one of the best turn based strategy games of all time, and makes an excellent sequel to XCOM Enemy: UnknownSet 20 years after the previous game we learn that the aliens have officially taken over earth, and now XCOM is fighting as a resistance movement using a mobile base known as ""The Avenger"", an advanced alien ship to launch their operations from.There are some new features to the game as well as improved features from the previous remake.- Because the Avenger is a mobile air base, the player can move around the globe. Each country will have a certain amount of regions in it, you have to spend intell which is a new currency to make contact with these new regions. Each region will give you a different bonus, (similar to Enemy Unknown) as well as extra income at the end of each month.- There are 4 new classes in the game. The ranger replaces the Assault class, and uses a shotgun for close range combat, they also carry a machette for melee combat.- The engineer can be used to hack objectives from a distance, or heal their own companions, or perform a battle scan which is very useful in the field.- The grenadier uses a light machinegun with a grenade launcher as a sidearm, while the snipers favour snipers (obviously) and a handgun.- Retalliation missions have replaced terror missions, they are much more challenging and tough to comnplete.- Occasionally a UFO will land that can be assaulted for supplies as a side mission.- There will be 3 different guerilla operations, that the player can only choose one of to complete. This depends on what the player needs the most at the time in terms of rewards for completing these missions, for example one mission will reward them with intel and can counter a certain dark event.- Dark events are 3 random events each month that work against the players favour.- The customisation for the soldiers is greatly improved, we can name our guns, as well as change their patterns. We can give our soldiers a background story, and change their attitudes overall.- The main aim is to prevent the Aliens Avatar project from being completed which can be slowed down overtime by destroying alien blacksite facilities or completing story mission objectives.- The story has been greatly improved as well, answering more questions and delivering us with more cinematic cutscenes.While I did not encounter many bugs with this title, its one of my top 3 games of 2016 and has a bunch of great mods, replay-ability and a decent amount of hours worth. Theres nothing like seeing your entire squad slaughter or get slaugtered by a bunch of aliens in the field, especially when you named them after your friends and family (or famous actors) cough cough 10/10"
