,Not Recommended,268500,30690845,Posted: 23 March,all,MichalRehacek,"The game features some nice updates since the first part: hacking, soldier customization, even the increase in difficulty and the change in settings where you are always being pursued by the aliens (which I personally do not like, but am willing to accept). Visuals look great too. If I were to base my review just on gameplay, the review would be positive.However, the game is still very buggy, even though it's been a long time since the original release. This is the reason why my review is going ot be negative. It has problems setting resolution (requiring me to reset the game resolution every time I launch it), the support for gamepads is buggy (I don't use a gamepad, but I have a few joysticks connected and the game assumes I'm using them, even though I have Mouse as the control scheme - the buggy controller support results in inability to name saves, because edit boxes behave as if the left arrow were pressed all the time), the game crashes once in a while - and those are just the biggest problems. These problems seem to have been known for a long time, so it doesn't look like they are going to be fixed ever.Then there are a few intentional interface design decisions that make things difficult. Texts are rendered on floating screens with a pulsating random effects - making it painful (literally) for someone like me, whose eyes are not perfect. Fortunately, this can be turned off by directly editing the config files. The transitions between different parts of the ship interface may look great, but seeing the same transitional 5-second animation for the 50th time during an evening isn't fun. And again, there's more.So overall, the gameplay is great, but the technical problems make the game so much worse than it could be. Thumb up for just the game contents, but thumbs down for the technical problems, resulting in an overall thumbs down."
