,Not Recommended,268500,21396141,"Posted: 22 February, 2016",all,-hg- stuv101,"There's a lot wrong with this game; to much to make it a valid 60 dollar purhase at this point.GameplayThe Random Number Generating system (RNG) is absolutely broken and completely rediculous. From what i understand, the RNG is a single element that applies to all XCOM units and ADVANT forces regardless of the circumstances.For example: lets say you have a Ranger unit within 3 spaces of a target thats out of cover, and you have a 95% chance to hit; this Ranger then misses for some stupid reason. you can load from the auto save and try again, but now anyone is garanteed to miss the first exchange regardless of who attacks first and regardless of ""hit percentages"".This type of situation can result in some pretty ridiculous kills. My best kill was a critical hit with a shotgun at it's maximum hitting distance, through a full cover wall; and that was an 11% chance to hit and 2% to critical it (AND THAT WAS REPEATABLE FROM THE AUTO SAVE!). Seriously, if that doesn't show how bad the RNG is in this game, I don't know what will.Every XCOM class is unbalanced, overpowered, or completely useless. The XCOM classes have a handful of useful classes: snipers, medics, demolition, heavy gunner, and psi op; every other class is completely worthless unblended (putting all your class points in one skill tree) and will get your team killed.The Combat Technician (combat hacker) gets the ability to hack mech units, shock enemies with a drone (minimal damage at best) and do local scans to find enemies within proximity of the user; Medics can heal, revive, and resurrect from a distance (that in itself is extremely overpowered, no need to keep the medic close by), and can get the ability to do all that to everyone on your team, all at one time, once per mission.The Gunslinger (Pistol Popper) can use their pistol (not main weapon) to shoot multiple enemies, shoot multiple shoot at one target, and take a pistol shot before using their main weapon (really the only good ability they have). Snipers can shoot at multiple enemies with a more powerful weapon, set up killzones (overwatch on crack), obliterate armor or near instakill (deadeye), and shoot from anywhere as long as someone has eyes on the target.The Blademasters and phantom skills need to be blended in order for rangers to be any good (if you didn't do this, good luck).Alien units are Unbalanced and OP. There are a lot of Aliens you will hate to fight in XCOM 2; mainly: Sectoids, Gatekeepers, Shieldbearers, Vipers, and Codex.Sectoids have a huge variety of psi abilities and sometimes use more than one in a turn.Gatekeepers are tank-like psi enemies with huge AoE attacks and laser eyes.Shieldbearers can turn any aliens around them into tanks or better tanks.Vipers can spit venom like thinmen, and grab units with a long tongue like Smokers from L4D (btw, their snakes, not frogs, wtf, they shouldn't have a tongue ability).codex can copy themselves, teleport, and AoE disarm units.The timers are stupid and make no sense in certain missions. Why do I have a timer for a rescue mission or an assassination mission? Why is there a timer for stealing enemy intel from a box or computer?Release QualityThe game was released in an unoptimized state. It's glitchy, slow, and can crash pretty hard from time to time. I had to start three missions over because my autosaves were corrupted, and restart the game at the final mission to fix some texture issues.ConclusionThis game needs some serious overhauls and patches; the game is down right frustrating with the current RNG and game mechanics, and is a chore to get though.Wait till this game gets an update, patches, overhaul mods / DLC, and a drop in price to no more than $30.It's not a bad game, it's an ungraceful game that needs some serious reworking."
