76561197998468672,Not Recommended,268500,21012380,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,[F]Ossoona,"TL;DR: Good, but buggy, not recommended for now - as good as the core game is, the bugs make it too frustratingMechanically, the game is fine - plays like the first one for the most part, with a few changes I would consider improvements, such as the ""Concealment"" system which - at least to some extent - makes overwatch crawling unnecesary for the first part of most missions.I, for one, like the ""dumbed down"" base building, seeing as in the first one, it didn't feel deep, it just felt needlessly complicated, but of course that's a matter of opinion.However, I've run into a lot of really annoying problems, mostly with the UI - not only does it seem poorly designed in a lot of cases, it also flat out breaks a lot. This includes stuff like not being able to click on buttons or icons for skills and mismatched tooltips.But I could deal with that stuff - it's just annoying, not really game ending.I will not recommend though, not until the number of bugs I (and apparently quite a few others) have run into.In my last session, all of a sudden, research and buildings stopped popping up when done. I didn't think much of it - the UI does a terrible job of conveying information at other times, so I figured I'd just misunderstood, and they simply weren't complete after all.But then I went to look, and construction timers and wound timers had gone into negative values - I had a facilty with a due time of ""-195 hours"", and soldiers with ""-4 days"" recovery, and I couldn't do anything with it, until all of a sudden I got spammed with alerts of completed stuff all over the place.In a game with fairly strict time and resource management, that's just not okay.Other than that, I frequently get ""blackouts"" during missions, where the screen turns grey with a red outline and only the HUD visible. The game still runs, and it will recover after a short while, but I just can't see what the enemy is doing, even though they're in my vision range.Then there's the framerate tanking, which I've seen quite a few people report here and there - it's simply atrocious. I'm running on a high end rig, I should not be seeing 15-20 frames.And whose brilliant idea was it to keep excessive screen shake in the game. One mission had a very strong shake throughout several of my turns. I kept my cursor completely still, but the shake of the screen meant that I was switching between 4 seperate tiles at random, making it really difficult to throw a grenade properly to hit 3 enemies.A lot of people are reporting crashes and shader errors, and the inability to quit the game without it crashing and mocking about - I get around this issue through the magic of Alt + F4.I want to keep playing, because the game is good. But the bugs are making it really annoying, and I will therefore in stead recommend picking it up at a later date.Edit: As a lot of people have pointed out, the game involves a lot of ""timed"" missions - many more than the first one. I'd be okay with that, if it didn't feel like there were just slightly too few turns to do stuff - if you step out in the wrong direction, you'll likely simply not have enough turns to get to the objective.I've rushed through missions, putting my soldiers in really dangerous positions and taking out targets as quickly as I could, but a lot of the time, they get reinforcements at the last second. So even when I rush, I usually get to the objective with 1 or 2 turns left, which is just barely enough for me to also ""activate"" the objective.The very highest I've had left (and I save-scummed on that one) was 4. The margin for error relative to the price of failure just seems off on many of the timed missions. But hey, maybe you're into that, in which case: Go nuts, you'll love it."
