76561198093215211,Not Recommended,268500,22532550,"Posted: 20 April, 2016",all,Robertson Crusoe,"This game plays like a bad joke, literally. You will have the feeling that somebody is telling you a bad joke or that you suddenly became part of a trashy movie. XCOM EU/EW were pretty cartoonish to some extend, but this game feels like it is the Goat Simulator of the XCOM series. And on top of that, all the hefty bugs make it even worse.It all begins in the tutorial that does not seem to end at any point of the game. You will be FORCED to make dumb moves and you will be forced to let two people die in order to learn how the game works. That is the first ""haha"" in your face and the prelude of the horrible joke that this game actually is. The second thing you will notice is that you will be told that you are ""concealed"" which will grant you a huge bonus: The element of surprise. That is not only a lie, it is a joke in itself. Because the next thing you will do is, you will plan out your ambush. Only to understand that when you fired the first bullet, all the enemies grant one free turn, again. The worst things of XCOM EU/EW have been made even worse. There is no element of surprise. Once one of your guys fires/is spotted/jumps through a window, all of your units are unconcealed. There is no combined ambush, no group surprise attack.Than you will learn the next important thing: Hit chances are also a joke. A parody. Lines of sights are completely broken, the cover system has no purpose and the hit chances should just be ignored. This is the only tactical game I know that punishes the player for smart actions and motivates him to just randomly ♥♥♥♥ around. Really, once you stopped caring for the hit chances, your hits will skyrocket. Ever since I just took every 41% hit chance, my overall hits went up to 75%. Flanking is broken aswell. There is one effective way to flank the enemy: Put a soldier right next to him. The rest is highly ineffective or sometimes does not work at all. There can be a clear line of sight from 2 metres away with no cover in your soldiers direction and the hit chance is 35% without any flanking bonus. Oh, that is another joke: Ignore the lines of sight. Yeah, your sniper cannot actually see the enemy, but squuuuadsight. Just take the shot and watch your sniper aim at the air, firing through 2 walls and blast this stupid enemy away. It is a joke. A parody  afterall. So just do random stuff.The maps are small. In EU/EW the maps were small, but you had time. In this game, you have timers all over the place. Active timers, passive timers, non-sensical timers. If you don't have a clear 8 turns timer, you will face a situation where the enemies are already killing civillians/shooting at some sort of goodie and so on. That is a timer as well. Even the loot items have timers. ""It seems the aliens have programed their equipment to self-destruct"". This, ... this is one of those lines that actually made my laugh. This is the moment you know, you are watching a crappy movie written by untalented, lazy writers. ""How do we add more timers?"" - ""I dunno, man. Wait, how about we make the equipment go boom in 3 turns?"" - ""Awesome!"". This is so cheap, it is hard to talk about it without making this game look like a total piece of crap. And the game is littered with stuff like that. The soldier that does not hit from 2 metres away will comment his failure with ""Adjusting aim"". Yeah. You just can't hit♥♥♥♥♥♥ Don't blame the gear. Your entire crew, whether it be the scientist, the tinker or the creepy guy that loves to call you ""commander"", will all lament on how you do not have time and you gotta rush, while you cannot do anything except listen to them, telling you in eeeendless paragraphs, that you don't have time. These contradictions make the game funny in a total unfunny way. You will be called ""commander"" all the time, but everybody will tell you what to do and the game will take away your control whenever it can.Sorry, I was talking about the small maps. Every map is a small rectangle. If you start in the lower right, there will be a troop of enemies in the lower left, the upper left and the upper right. That is it. End of transmission. To not trigger them all at once, so that 12 enemies get one free turn to get in perfect cover, you will always attack one troop full frontal. You have to. Time is running out and bla, bla. So, there is not much tactic in the game. You do what takes the enemy out of the game as quickly as possible.  So every map will be the same.Thin men suddenly became reptile aliens. I mean, just ... is it ... I cannot. That is dumb beyond any reason. The weakish thin men used their form to infiltrate humanity. In one of the cutscenes you see a thin man shaking hands with some sort of politician. A 3 metres high guy, looking like a giant. How can those people infiltrate humanity? And if they are viper things in reality, why did we not see any viper before? They are so awesome, they will pull your soldiers from behind full cover, through a wall and 2 cars across half of the map right into the enemy line. And than, you have another timer.The enemy AI is dumb as can be. It is not difficult to battle them mentally. It is difficult to mentally endure the artificial way this game was made difficult. If you fight a tank with a pea shooter, yeah, that will be hard. Impossible even. The XCOM AI is not smart, it will always take the same actions it did before. But is has better gear, does not care for your cover, has uber awesome skills, can take turns during your turns and when the glitches and bugs set it, they can even fly and melee attack your soldiers through walls and stuff. There are some enemies, that will have a turn every time you do anything. Literally anything. Or, when your soldier fails to hack the red light towers, the enemy does get insta-reinforcements. Right in the middle of your turn a spaceship will land and boom, here they are. All these facts combined turn the game into a huge, goofy parody of EU/EW. It will ask you to just rush and take dumb movements. Whenever you try to play smart, it will hit you in the face and go all ""haha"" on you. It will take away your control every ♥♥♥♥♥ing time it can. You will constantly switch between menues, because your scanning for this or that gets interrupted by ""hey look at me"".There is only one thing, this game is good for: If you like to create purple and pink pimps and strippers in pink fedoras with pink weapons, this is your game. Literally, that is the main strength of the game: The customization. It encourages you to go all joker on this game. And than you laugh yourself into stupidity while watching your pink grenadiers with sunglasses whip the enemy. Sadly, this is all there is. A big, fat, sad joke. A bad movie that plays a heroic soundtrack. A huge contradiction and sadly, if this has become XCOM now, I'd rather not see a third part of this series. I feel ashamed and insulted when I play this game. And that is why I could not force myself to finish it. I tried two times, I just can't endure all the crazy stuff I paid 50 bucks for.I would not recommend this game to anyone, at any time for any reason and price. A product, so flawed should be shunned."
