76561198291357796,Recommended,268500,33119335,Posted: 2 July,all,+SuperJesus+,"""THIS GAME IS TOO STRESSFUL ITS FULL OF TIMERS AND I CANT TAKE IT! ""-Every negative review.Ok this game is a hard game. Xcom is about learning and having your decisions matter if you build the wrong building first or take too long to do something or have half or more of your core drop team wounded for weeks it can mean the end of your campaign. How do you solve this you ask? SAVE! I learned after playing Enemy Unknown that you wanna save after every mission and have at least 4 saves so if you screw something up or realize you built the wrong building or lose a team member or whatever you can go back.My first playthrough of Xcom 2 was about 16 hours before I realized that I could build the guirilla tactics school and increase my sqaud size lol So I took out 2 black sites and did all sorts of missions with 4 people and I was thinking ""DAMN! The negative reviews are real! This game is way too hard!"". Needless to say I have a new one going and Im doing just fine. Your decisions matter in this game and know your resources and what you want and plan ahead.Now the TIMERS! THE GOD AWEFUL DREADED TIMERS! AAAAAAAAAAAAAAH! Ill be completely honest here guys they are alittle stressful and it seems like when you first play that there will always be timers and the avatar clock haunting you. After you rid yourself of the first 3 black sites (make sure you make contact w/ territories leading to them or the ones where they are FIRST!) the timer is basically at zero then you have to do 2 skull jack missions after you decipher the codex which subtract 3 bars each or 2 for one and 3 for the other and you have alot of breathing room. For me I didnt let the avatar project go past the halfway marker, I would take a black site out matbe get alil resources upgrade something then go to the next and it was EASY! Especially with more than 4 member in your deployment team lol And Im not gonna go into the mission 