dn't have much fun despite being excited for the game and that kind of gameplay. 12 hours in i still have no idea, what am i doing and what are my priorities. My actions have very vague impact on overall situation. Difficulty goes uphill pretty fast, but i feel helpless. I don't get it, whole base managment part - by what criteria i should make choices on my research, production, building and contacts. Game spend a lot of time teaching me how to move soldiers, but zero time teaching any valid tactics to put in a right direction. It feels like i can do any concious decisions only after beating the game, preferably several times. Until then, my choices are pretty much blind."
