76561198058156743,Recommended,268500,23354525,"Posted: 2 June, 2016",all,Inspector Dosh,"I gotta admit, I was playing on a very low end laptop playing at around 10-15 fps so I won't really touch on performance and what not. For those who are not familiar with the Xcom franchise, it is a series of turn-based tactical games that is well known for its unforgiving difficulty. The Xcom games made from Firaxis are made as a reboot to the series after when everyone thought the franchise was seemingly dead and was made for people who are both new and old to the franchise with of course easier difficulty levels added in to keep newer player from getting discouraged from joining Xcom while the higher difficulties are of course there for the veterans, although I've never played the originals myself.So what does Xcom 2 add in from Enemy Unknown? Here's a short list to get an idea:-new enemy types, with ADVENT troops being the sucessor to the EXALT forces in Enemy Within and a few new aliens and the old aliens learning a few more tricks up their sleaves-base defence, for when the aliens are able to attack your mobile command center-semi-procedural level generation-new and improved class abilities-the ability to save your customized soldiers in a separate list so you can play with them throughout multiple games-weapon customization as a separate upgrade system instead of taking up a utility slot along with visual upgrades (like taking a scope replacing gadgets like medkits and grenades)-Steam Workshop SupportSome negatives to consider:-PC requirements are pretty high so double check to see if you meet the requirements-$60 USD as opposed to Enemy Unknown for $30 USD, unless you buy the Enemy Within expansion for $30 USD without a sale-people have said something about the AI doing stupid things every now and again, but I wouldn't really know for sure because I'm bad at this game-some visual glitches with soldiers and aliens alike doing some pretty weird things from time to time-don't even bother with the multiplayerHonestly, I feel too lazy to even say anymore since there are way better reviews than this one and there really isn't any reason to repeat what people have already said for about 10,000 times. Would I recommend Xcom 2? For someone who's fairly new to the Xcom franchise, I enjoyed my time with it immensely so what reason do I have to say no other than the negatives I mentioned above along with easy access to mods via the Steam Workshop extending the games' lifespan."
