,Recommended,268500,21035269,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,daddy,"Oh boy, this is a difficult one. People have already spoken about the performance issues, but with a beefy system they are just a cosmetic nuisance. As are the occasional crashes. The real problems lie elsewhere...And they aren't new. This game is at its core, despite all the gameplay differences, very similar to EW, for better or for worse. It is still a tabletop/boardgame in how it plays, all important factors are decided by banal dicerolls. You could argue that point blank missing a 90% shot and then dying is part of xcom identity and that's a fair argument I guess. But the game did not only not reduce the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t RNG, it now shoves more of it in your face. In the overworld map enemy activity constitutes primarily of a random percentual increase in what is essentially ""panic"" which can completely ♥♥♥♥ you on higher difficulty. Regardless of how frustrating it can be, it's so incredibly uncreative and low effort.Generally difficulty is manageable, you can easily keep your soldiers alive through commander (classic diff. equivalent) without savescumming (too much ;). The ""shaken"" mechanic is extremely annoying in the beginning but ultimately very manageable once you exit the beginning difficulty spike by virtue of leveling up your soldiers.Combat too is the same old. It is virtually unchanged compared to EW. Seems a bit lazy that certain things (e.g. not being able to cancel overwatch after an enemy was revealed, unskippable animations !!!) weren't adressed. The round timers everyone ♥♥♥♥♥ themselves about are a complete non issue. However I agree that there would have been better ways to disincentivize overwatch whoring, for example increase reward for quick completion. Same with the accuracy, why not make a lowish (~50%) acc shot guarantee a hit but with low damage? Unfortunately the devs took the familiar, easy way out which really is the plague of this game.Game's also fun though. Customization, Story delivery and Visuals are much improved from EW while still having the same feel. It adds a lot of personality and it's great that you can get attached to your ship and soldiers this way. It's just so sad that this isn't any more than graphics/content update similar to how EW was to EU. Why do I recommend it then? Most things are easily fixable with mods, and mod support is one thing Firaxis have done very right!"
