,Recommended,268500,20987400,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Senior_Whiffage,"Let's address the elephant before we push it out of the room.The sheer number of timed missions are a questionable design decision. I'm not entirely against them - it's new, takes some getting used to, and adds a sense of urgency to your missions. Despite how lovingly you remember it, creeping slowly across a map in full overwatch was boring in XCOM:EO. A simple fix would seem to be: start the time when concealment breaks. That way I can position my units accordingly and choose when to begin the countdown.Next is performance. I have a Core i7 and GTX 980 graphics card and the game runs abysmally on high settings. The nice thing about both of these complaints is that they can be patched and modded away.The game is otherwise fantastic. More of what you love about the XCOM series with some new additions. The procedurally-generated randomness is great and I enjoy that no two playthroughs will ever be the same. Looting upgrades and other items in the field is a wonderful touch. I look forward to finishing my first playthrough, and many more to come."
