,Not Recommended,268500,21376347,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,enRAGEd,"This is the first time I actually get around to writing a ""review"" on Steam - let's say I felt compelled.I could write a thorough review where I could present my analysis of the game, and I can tell you right now that it would be mostly positive... after all, the tried and tested gameplay dynamics of EU are thoroughly implemented in XCOM 2, which is exactly what many of us were hoping for, and that alone is a major selling point (at least for me).However, the unfortunate reality is that I find that the game as it stands is not even WORTHY of a review of that kind of nature, because it has not AT ALL been optimized... it plays like an early beta (and even that is a generous statement).For this price tag, I expect at the very least a stable and mostly seamless game in terms of functionality (with exception to large-scale, open world games like F4, Skyrim and the likes where unique bugs are unavoidable due to the sheer magnitude of possible executions). XCOM 2 seamless? Not. Even. Close.Aside from the annoying lack of graphics optimization which causes at times severe drops to FPS, there are shading problems, jittering and a plethora of other issues that affect gameplay... but that, folks, isn't even the worst part.The game has a mind-bogglingly high crash-frequency, and it's impossible to determine most of the causes. Sometimes the game stops working, other times it just closes, and on rare occasions, it actually induces a fatal error in the system causing a blue screen or otherwise forcing a hard reboot. I have NEVER seen the likes of it, and I've done everything in my power on the user side to resolve, or rather mitigate the problems, to absolutely no avail.The crashes have been a show-stopper for many users trying to get in on the noble quest to save the Earth... but, not all.Be advised, if you buy this game, there is a very good chance it will be practically unplayable to you. If you do experience crashes early, immediately get a refund before it's too late, because you more than likely not be able to resolve the issues.TL;DR: XCOM 2 is virtually unplayable due to terrible optimization, and I cannot with a clear conscience recommend this game to anyone at its current quality, especially at the shameful price. I look forward to the patch.EDIT:To date, it's been exactly six months since I made my original review, and I figured I'd try out XCOM 2 again. There's a multitude of different mods, and a series of new DLCs added since the game came out, and I wanted to give it a run.During my first runthrough six months ago, I actually ended up pushing through the game (despite crashing an uncountable amount of times a day). Why? Well, the game IS entertaining, and even though I suffered through hours trying to fix the crashes to no avail, as well as countless restarts due to those very same crashes, I still wanted to get through it. Hey, it was too late for a refund...Now I'm back, and I didn't dream that the game would still be suffering issues... and yet it did. After copious amounts of research (here we effing go again), there seems to be no solution or even trigger for the most common crash, the one that I'm also experiencing. In addition, there seems to be no indication that Firaxis, to be frank, gives one iota of a♥♥♥♥♥♥(it's been happening since the Shen's Last Gift DLC, it would seem).Unbelievable. It sucks that I couldn't change my review.GG Firaxis, (GisRunning == 1) is OP, no re."
