,Not Recommended,268500,21359810,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,Nightwave,"It pains me to write this, considering that I'm a very huge fan of Enemy Unknown. I confess that I have not played any of the other titles, but that's an irrevelant point.While the core mechanics and gameplay are solid, as well as nice visual, I cannot recommend the game in its current state. As noted, there are many instances of hiccups and awkward in-game delays. For example, after a unit is killed, there is a rather lengthy pause. I also experienced clipping/invisible enemies on the map. Some of these issues are not entirely gamebreaking though, but it is rather jarring. The pre-mission loading screen takes too long, and if you read the other reviews, you'll find out more issues.It also doesn't help that the chance to hit relies entirely on RNG. I'm not sure where to begin. But the aim/hit system is incredibly inconsistent. Throughout the majority of the game, I lost count how many ""misses"" I experienced on our end. My sharshooter has missed plenty of ""90% hit"" shots. I also notice that enemies such as Vipers (from across the map) have better firing on my team than vice versa. I'm also not sure how the ""positioning/aiming"" system actually works, but there were instances where I would come around a covering, only to find that I would have a less than 70% chance of killing an EXPOSED enemy a few tiles ahead of me.I also notice that the game really throws everything at you from the get-go. More often than not, you'll be stuck with rookie soldiers on your first playthrough. I love playing tactically, and spamming my Overwatch just to be sure, but these time-based missions force you to rush against the constant assault by the enemy. It wouldn't be so bad, but they throw in these Sectoids of whom have an extreme high range of panicking/mind controlling your squad. There is certainly an unforgiving pace, but only for the wrong reasons. The first game had a perfect balance and pace, but this just seems to really throw the nuke at you when you're not careful.If it weren't for the mods adding a support class and allowing benched soldiers XP, I probably wouldn't have gotten as far as I did. Not only does the game need a technical patch, they really need to reevaluate some of the balancing in the enemies and allow current players some breathing room. I pity the ironmen out there."
