ock of three houses.Come on, my slingshot at home has a greater range (and probably damage) than that stupid sniper rifle.Dito for other classes.The Ranger class that has amazing cinematographics for the first few times they strike down an enemy. After that the enemies become far too tough for that stupid useless toothpick of even the most advanced swordtype to do squat against virtually any enemy except the weakest. And the Ranger's shotgun requires the Ranger to be almost on top of the enemy.Yeaaaah, great. Why not give me a spear and a sling with stones. Maybe I would actually get a better range with that than with my shotgun.Psionic soldiers, errr operatives, that require a clear view of the enemy AND also nearly have to be up close and personal. Blaargh.Nah, don't make me go into more detail.The ranges and even the best upgrades in the tech tree totally suck.6) Bugs and balancing issues still riddle this crash fest of a game.I don't know how often the game crashed during my one play-thru. But I lost count at around 30.When did Firaxis subscribe to the current gaming industry standard of releasing seriously unfinished and untested product?7) And finally, an ending that was so anti-climactic that it nearly put me to sleep.Oh boy, are you guys gonna be surprised the first time you see it.It probably was one of the worst endings in the full UFO series I have ever seen.Nah, not worth it.Forget about this game. Maybe when, or rather IF, some of the Long War modders have finalized a full game overhaul of the complete logic then you might consider this game.But only once this game has landed in the bargain bin of Steam.Cause I wouldn't pay $10 for it in its currents state.But even the most amazing mod won't bring interceptors back again.Sad, sad state of afairs for the gaming industry."
