76561198071215446,Recommended,268500,23478585,"Posted: 9 June, 2016",all,Artisan Cheese,"TL;DR at the bottomIm gonna be totally honest, im giving this game a positive review because there isnt an ""its ok"" rating.I absolutely loved XCOM: EU and I'm a huge fan of tactial combat and strategy games. Not only did i sink quite a bit of time into XCOM: EU, but i actually bought the iOS version so i could play it when im away from my computer.Like a lot of other fans of XCOM, when i saw XCOM 2 announced and i saw all the trailers for how the game looked and how much more stuff there was going to be in XCOM 2, I almost♥♥♥♥♥♥my pants in excitement. I preordered the game and I was so ♥♥♥♥ing ready to play this game. You can imagine how upset i was when the game launched and was practically unplayable because it ran like♥♥♥♥♥♥for so many people. I was willing to wait however, because i knew this game was going to be great.Promptly after the Launch Day issues were resolved, a lot of people were saying that the game was unplayable, and to an extent, it still is. XCOM 2 is arguably one of the most difficult and punishing squad-based tactical combat strategy games on the market today. When the game first launched and everyone was talking about XCOM 2, i heard a lot of statements that followed the general idea of ""XCOM 2 is the Dark Souls of combat strategy games"".THIS IS ABSOLUTELY 100% TRUE.Much like dark souls, XCOM 2 does not give a♥♥♥♥♥♥about your precious little feelings. ""Im sorry to hear that you missed with a 99% chance to hit, but you're still going to die here""  Clearly, there is a lot of XCOM:EU still reminiscent in XCOM 2, but there also isn't. This is why i feel so torn about giving this game a positive review, because i cant give it a neutral review, but i don't think it deserves a negative review. Let me run through the pros and cons real quick.Pros:+Excellent turn-based strategy that you know from XCOM:EU+Abundant customization options (who wouldn't want to slice sectiods in half while wearing a top-hat and monocle?)+DIVERSITY (good lord are there a lot of different enemy types in XCOM 2, which is something that i wish XCOM:EU had. I get that there are elite type enemies in XCOM:EU, but in the end theyre pretty much the same enemies, but stronger. XCOM 2 has a large variety of completely different enemies that have their own seperate abilities, armors, weapons, hopes, dreams, etc.)+MELEE COMBAT (why wasn't this is the vanilla XCOM:EU?)+Mod Support (idk about you guys, but if you arent saving the world as Guy Fieri, Shrek, John Cena, and Hatsune Miku, i think youre playing this game wrong)~Unbalanced Gameplay (I love an uphill battle, and i totally understand that an uphill battle is exactly what the devs were going for when they made the game. After all, youre the resistance. You dont have military-grade stuff, so naturally the enemy will have better weapons and equipment. I put this as an iffy kind of thing as many people might be upset about the steep difficulty curve.)~Lack of customization options (?) (honestly im not sure if this is the right way to put this, but i wish there were more basic styles for faces and hair. I kept getting recruits with the same faces, and i like to think that the resistance were only recruiting people from the same bloodline, but since those people kept dying, i dont think their bloodline would have lasted very long.)Cons:-HOLY♥♥♥♥♥♥THIS GAME IS HARD (I like an uphill battle, but this game is unfairly difficult. There's the obvious 99% chance to hit situation, but there has been more than one time where i was directly adjacent to an enemy and i had a 35% chance to hit with a melee attack. Not a ranged attack, a MELEE attack. Honestly, the swords would do better to just be a decorative piece than an actual weapon.)-Unoptimized (don't expect to be able to run this on any computer that could just barely run XCOM:EU)-Unoriginal Story line (I really do want to like the story of XCOM 2, but i would have greatly prefered a situation where we did defend earth, but they came back in greater numbers, like the new independence day movie.)-Less than (inter)Stellar voice acting (I didnt find Tygan or Lily to be super interesting characters. Like, i understand that  XCOM:EU's Dr.Shen would have taken a major stand against the alien forces and died doing such, but I find it a little odd that his daughter, who apparently would have been a little girl during the events of XCOM:EU, grew up to do the exact same thing as her father, with the exact same, if not more, skill as her father. Also, where the hell did Dr.Vahlen go? RIP(?))I feel like a lot of the points I've made about the game's difficulty could be best sumarrized by the Best Friends Play XCOM 2 series. I believe there are 7 parts to the series, but im probably wrong about that. They do a great job of going into greater depth about a lot of the topics i've covered here, but then again, theyre considerably bigger losers than i am.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rpAdhLcuSjkTL;DRIn the end i have to give this game a 7.5/10If you like games with a 90 degree difficulty curve, smashing keyboards out of anger, and beating your head against a brick wall until you or the wall falls, then you will love this game.Also it helps if youre a fan boy of XCOM:EU and Dark Souls like I am."
