76561197972199106,Recommended,268500,20962514,"Posted: 4 February, 2016",all,Fullbordad,"Will update this once I get home from work, review mostly written for old xcom players.+ The combat has been improved a lot because of small things that makes the game have a much better pacing. As an example they've added the ability to actually see if you have a line of sight on the enemies so that you wont have to worry about it when moving around.+ The new system in which you spawn invisible to the enemies makes the first part of every map more enjoyable because it means you're setting up ambushes instead of hoping for good rng with the pod openings.+ I for one like the new base building system even if it at first glance might look dumbed down. It feels like you wont have to play a certain way IE follow a certain building line that was always the same no matter what.+ So far the enemies have been fun and rewarding to face, and I'm eager to see what they will throw at me for the rest of the game.* Some graphical glitches like weapons or enemies clipping trough walls, pretty much the same as the previous game. It doesn't affect game play unless you really care about graphics.* Difficulty has been scaled down and it feels like if you would play on a difficulty level under commander(classic) it would probably be really easy compared to the previous game.- The AI has a habit of some times running into really stupid positions. As an example I've had two occasions now where AI ran into cars that exploded the next round, instantly killing them. Not sure if intented but I doubt it.- Terrible optimization makes the menu, cutscenes and base almost unplayable. I don't know if this is a common issue but my rig should easily be able to handle this on even the highest graphics. Luckily since it's a turn based game it doesn't affect game play that much.Easily recommend the game for now!"
,Not Recommended,268500,21016848,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Gitarkin,"This isn't turn based strategy, it's time management.Every mission has an objective on the other side of the map, that you'll have to retrieve/hack/destroy/etc.Standing in between you and that objective, is a large number of aliens. Sounds fun, right? Good news, it is!That is, until you realize that you're basically not allowed to strategize, due to the comically small time limit you're given to complete these missions. You have a very small amount of turns, to not only achieve your objective, but in some cases, kill off all the remaining enemies on the map. What does this mean? It means rather than sneaking around and being careful in order to achieve a successful attack (aka ""strategy""), you will be making a suicidal dive towards the objective in hopes of getting out in time. This makes gameplay extremely linear, and leads to the inevitable and needless death of countless squad members.Sadly, the time limit that plagues individual missions, plagues the entire campaign as well. I don't want to spoil it for those who plan on getting this, but there is also a very small window to achieve certain events, and failure to do so means campaign over. I also found the side quests overwhelming and not fun at all. They bombard you with a million things all at once, all timed, with zero explanation. Failure to do these things will put you behind in resources, which in turn makes you less prepared on the battlefield. And let's face it, you're gonna get fisted out there on a good day.This game has a lot of potential, but it's poisoned by the fact that you're constantly being shoved from behind, rather than being allowed to enjoy what is otherwise, a beautiful game. If a patch or mod comes along, that fixes this ridiculous time mechanic, then I highly reccommend you pick it up. If not, save your money, because as of now it's Diner Dash with guns."
