,Recommended,268500,30819287,Posted: 29 March,all,Zero Summ,"Pros:Engaging turn-based combat. It's easy to pick up but you quickly realize how important every single action is. One wrong move could easily result in a dead soldier. There's also a good variety of classes (4 base classes, 1 unlocked via a ship upgrade, and another is part of Shen's Last Gift DLC.)Layers of strategy: I really like the tension the game maintains. Having to choose between squad or ship upgrades, or what continent you should help first. The game has a surprising amount of depth to it.Mod support: This game has a wonderful modding community behind it. There is a huge selection of content: character customization props, addition terrain pieces, quality of life fixes, additional classes, and campaign overhauls.(On a side note: avoid any character props/races that have ""empty"" face placeholders. I.e. they only have eyes, teeth, and hair. The game will still use those for randomly generated NPCs, engineers, and scientists. That♥♥♥♥♥♥is nightmare fuel.)Character customization: Honestly, I think I spent 8 hours just making characters. There is a pretty decent selection just in the vanilla game. Add mods that allow for additional layering and more pieces and you can do pretty much anything.Replayability: Very high. Trying out different mods, different play-styles, randomly generated events and battlefields, and different upgrade priorities. No two games will be the same.Graphics & sound: The game has respectable AAA graphics and sound. Plenty of options, and runs smoothly. While the game does look good, it probably won't blow anyone away.Neutral:Story: It won't blow your mind by any measure, but the story maintains a good focus and the cut-scenes, characters, and voice acting are all well executed and maintain a good production quality.Environmental destruction: Walls, trees, and clutter items are all destructible, I just wish buildings had more dynamic destruction. Like if you took out some support beams the whole building would go down.Difficulty curve: The game goes from ""walk-in-the-park"" to ""this game is horse♥♥♥♥♥♥quot; difficulty real quick. Though, once you kind of know what your doing it's not so bad.Cons:Line of sight issues: even with mods that provide some additional feature and bug fixes, this is probably the most frustrating part of the game. Nothing will generate rage like getting one-shot through the floorboards when on your turn your character couldn't even see them.The game is still pretty buggy. On a totally vanilla game I've ran into bugs like: enemies don't take actions, and SPARK units don't end turn after using overdrive, and all their actions.Hacking mechanic: Rewards are sometimes nonsensical, and usually don't warrant the risk/reward until you get a higher level technician. I just didn't find the mechanic fun.Computer Specs: Intel i7 5930k, EVGA GTX 1080ti FE, LG 34UM95 (3440x1440, 60hz), 500GB Samsung 850 Pro SSD."
