,Recommended,268500,34336383,Posted: 18 August,all,The Outsider,"XCOM 2 is half turn based tactics game, with some RPG elements, and half real-time ""strategic"" base/guerrilla warfare management sim.Basis of the game is you're humans, and the aliens have taken Earth. It is fully under their control, and you're the fringe element now. You have to lead soldier boiz and grrllz to victoly against the aliens in hit and run operations.It's pretty solid, definitely better now than it was, and a couple leagues above it's predecessors--however, there isn't much more here than there was in XCOM 1: Enemy Within. If you like that, you'll love this.In addition, the modding scene for this game is alive and thriving, and a new expansion for the game is available, which adds more factions, classes, and sillier stuff you can do with your soldiers. The expansion is currently priced at ~$40.00 USD, which I think is a little bit too expensive for the amoun of stuff they added, so definitely wait until that goes on sale.Multiplayer is pretty much PvP, your team vs another player's team--either humans or aliens. This is a pretty singleplayer-focused game.If you like turn based tactics or strategy games, you'll probably like this game. It has it's bugs and quirks, such as people hitting an enemy with a regular shot through three walls, etc. But they generally don't break the game."
