76561198008893862,Recommended,268500,28121832,"Posted: 1 December, 2016",all,Old-Painless,"I did not buy this game until it was on sale. I read so many negative reviews about ""timers"" and how it was ""buggy"". If you liked the first reboot, there is nothing you will not love about this game. I regret having waited months before getting this game. It is virtually identical to the first, but all the new features are meaningful and interesting - I would not call them gimmicks. Disregard all these negative reviews that talk about performance issues, ""not enough time to build a strategy"" and general bugginess. When people say ""timer"", they mean a ""turn counter. Yes, many missions have a turn counter, but so did the first reboot. XCOM 2 makes it so you have to make tough decisions in a really interesting way - there is plenty of room for strategy. I would say XCOM 2 is punishingly difficult - which is part of why I loved the first reboot. I would say XCOM2 is definitely harder than the first, by a lot actually. The one thing I love about the XCOM series is that victory is dirty - you lose stuff you don't want to lose and you have to find a way to push on and adapt. I highly recommend this game and I highly recommend buying this game if you liked XCOM1. I rarely ever write reviews for games - I really listened to the reviews I read and they misled me on this one."
