76561197960846724,Recommended,268500,20976510,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Sancezzio,"Beat EU on Classic difficulty. Selected ""Veteran"" (normal difficulty) on XCOM 2. Failed the first mission twice. Would fail again 10/10EDIT:Honestly though, While in XCOM Enemy Unknown it was a long time before aliens appeared who could mind control your soldiers, in XCOM 2 they appear right from the very first mission. Sitting behind cover and trading fire with alien forces is no longer a tactic that will keep all of your squad alive. Be aware that if you think you knew XCOM, you'll need to be going in with a keen mind to relearn everything you thought you knew about XCOM tactics.Performance wise, I have a 2500k and a GTX 970 coupled with 16GB of RAM. The game just scrapes 60fps on High settings with SSAO turned down to ""Tile AO"", with major FPS drops whenever the CPU is being utilised, like between turns or during loading sequences. Maps which use a lot of fire effects (such as retaliation missions) never hit 60fps on my system.I thought I understood XCOM pretty well, but honestly this game has absolutely punished my complacency. I've had to restart my campaign due to a squad wipe on a very crucial mission, and even then I'm having difficulty keeping hold of veteran soldiers. Crucially though, I feel I am losing only because of my own incompetence rather than the game being weighted too unfairly. Sure, you get those ""really?!"" moments of chance that feel awful, but also you get really lucky sometimes so it's a balance."
