76561198109108692,Recommended,268500,21133138,"Posted: 11 February, 2016",all,fhfatpku001,"I am longwar fans (600+ h ),  I've been played this game for 20+ h. And sorry for my bad english.Suggestion: Do not start with Legendary + ironman, it's a new game, and they change the gameplay style in every aspect (tactic strategy, research tree, and research-gear relation, etc)So far I am pretty satisfied with all those IMPROVEMENTs. The reseaon I call it IMPROVEMENT rather than change are the following:1. Strategy: which is the most complaints about. However, to me, is not. Someone complain, there is always a timer for most of the games (maybe 7 out of 10). If you play longwar or vanilla, you spend a lot of time on searching the enemy, which is pretty boring. This may be is why they put a timer and decrease the map size, meanwhile increase the complexity. In this way, you just focus on ""what the hell, How could I get out of here safely?"" when you've done this, together with some LOOT, you will gain a lot of fun and sastisfactory. Every mission last for 20-30mins average. Some mission will last for 1 h. The game strategy rely more on your understanding of the following: a) Enviroment, not just cover and destroy cover, sometimes, a Perfects gernade will change everything (4+4 damage is possible!), especially in the start. there are many examples for you to discover. b) your understanding of the class builds, and every item(all of them are pretty useful), and each of the class plays its role in the gameplay. (compare with vanilla within, super hero-""sniper"") c)Playstyle is various, Overwatch is not always the best way to kill the enemy, so does ranger. you will always have more and better choices, there is not a unique pattern to follow. And this is also why I suggest not choose ironman at first, you can discover many strategies.2. DifficultyPersonally, I suggest longwar verterans starts with commander, famillar with  and gain some knowledge about the game(especially the research tree and mission choise). Because xcom 2 wiki is now under development, it's almost impossible to beat the legendary ironman.The Auto Save and Load design is pretty good, especially for those who rely on S/Ls. I mean, you never focus on when should I save? (S/L gurantee hits is a bad habit, xcom 2 will help you get rid of this)Find the diff level most suitable for you which also means minimize the S/L times. Be preparing for the final xcom experience ironman. (when xcom 2 wiki is complete, I will start Leg+ ironman)What do you think about Legendary Diff? I think it is suitable, but it's not for the beginners, seriously. If you are interested in that diff, you can search youtube, like Mr. Odd's(recommended), or some twitch channals.3. Research + ""New Foundry""-Proving Ground + Loot/Gear System.The new gear systems is pretty fun. the relation between those 3 is very neat. (I am pretty sure they gain the idea from LONGWAR). But I should say, there are still more space to improve.  Just enjoy it.4. Missions: Becareful about the choices, especially in Commander and Legendary Difficult.It's not just as easy as ""rush satallites"" in within. Someone complains about the design, think, I've been already super frustrated about the tactic strategy, can you give me some ""non-frustration"" time? Maybe this is a point for those modder and developer to think about.Currently the game design is: ""You will not have anytime to take a deep breath, aleins have already take control the world."" You must stop this, although it is ""IMPOSSIBLE"".5. Bugs: A Lot of bugs...crushes is pretty common. Some bugs are funny, like, sometimes the enemy are ""stunned"", you name it...So may be it's not  the time to start the ""Ultimate Xcom Experience: Ironman""LAST, I believe after some patches and mods, this game will become a ""must buy"".   Besides, there will be a LONGWAR mod to make it Legendary."
