,Recommended,268500,20981358,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Tudhalyas,"UPDATE 17/09/2016: After playing the game again with some performance patches and all the planned DLCs out, I can say that most performance issues have been solved and the game runs better than ever.My only gripe is about the DLCs. For the price that is being asked by 2K / Firaxis, the amount of content is certainly not much, especially when compared to what Enemy Within was for the original XCOM: Enemy Unknown game from 2012. Buy the DLCs only if you really, really, **really** want to or when the Deluxe edition of XCOM 2 is on sale. More info about the DLCs in my review for the XCOM 2 Reinforcement Pack.-----The king of turn-based strategic-tactical games is back, and it's better than ever!Imagine everything that makes XCOM Enemy Unknown the great game that it is, and make it even bigger: the strategic portion of the game has grown even more:1) now you don't have just to expand the Avenger -- your (mobile) base of operations -- but you have to consider a consistent lack of resources, both in terms of materials and manpower, which you mostly recruit through VIP extractions missions around the globe;2) you have to plan your moves carefully as conducting missions require moving the Avenger. This takes time, and time is most likely the most scarce resource of all, as the aliens now are much more active in trying to hinder XCOM's efforts, through the Avatar Project and the so-called Dark Events -- initiatives that either target XCOM directly, like a direct assault against the Avenger, or power-ups given to the ADVENT coalition troops.The tactical layer is also expanded and more interesting:1) the newly introduced concealment mechanic allows for the setup of ambushes;2) your troops can now be customized down to the tiniest detail, from their own physical appearance to their outfits; base weapons are now also further customizable through mods that you can retrieve through missions. A proper full inventory management isn't present, but this still feels way more satisfying than what XCOM:EU had to offer.3) ADVENT troops and their alien masters are absolutely terrifying and a challenge to tackle: they are more powerful, more aggressive and more intelligent than ever before. Prepare to defend against constant flankings!The only thing that prevents XCOM 2 from being perfect is a sub-optimal optimization for certain hardware configurations that will be surely fixed within a reasonable time.TL;DR: if you loved the previous game or you like tactical games in general, do yourself a favor and get this game!My vote: 9.5 / 10"
