,Recommended,268500,21051038,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,[bhtp]Ataman,"Rarely I write a review for a game, but I think this one earned it.First off: There is a lot of discontent going around, mainly because of the mission timers, doom timer and perfomance issues.I have a GTX 760 and while some perfomance drops are noticeable they don't really hinder your gameplay experience.The game certainly doesn't look incredible with AA turned off it's still nice to look at and fun to play. Also, since this is a Firaxis game you can pretty much expect a perfomance patch in the next few weeks or even days.The timers are a whole different subject. Many people hate them, so do I. From a logical standpoint, the timers are total ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t. Somehow the supply convoy you're about to raid is rigged to explode in a few minutes, despite the fact the enemy doesn't even know you're there. You're concealed after all. Reinforcements under way? Wait what? Reinforcement against whom? The unknown force which nobody knows about?The alien transmitter only has 8 turns left before it sends out all the data of your operations? It takes hours to get there but the transmitter always finishes a few minutes after your squad drops in. Since these turns would only take seconds in a real scenario this is completely ridiculous.Sadly however, many players just go ahead and moan all day instead of taking 2 minutes and get the DisableTimers mod from the workshop. (Or the TimerTweaks mod if you still want them but less stressful).Seriously, it's that easy, your problem is gone with the click of a button. Turn up your difficulty to compensate and you're set for a great experience without any illogical stress.The doom timer needs editing in the config files of the game which may be an issue for less experienced people but if you're willing to take that step you can tweak those as well. If you don't, no biggie, in my current experience on classic difficulty the doom timer doesn't seem to be that threatening. Don't get me wrong it's fast and really tries to stress you out but it gets much easier after learning how to deal with it.The doom timer, from a logical standpoint, is again totally illogical of course. It took the aliens 20 years to get there but now they're finishing in a few months.About the gameplay itself:If you liked XCOM:EU you will love this one. They took many features from the predecessor and fleshed them out. There are many improvements like the fact that you don't have to fabricate every piece single piece of armor. Instead you get your armor upgrades for everyone while still having to option for unique armor pieces through different means.All in all a great experience if you're willing to take 2 minutes before starting your campaign."
