76561197973296734,Recommended,268500,30606524,Posted: 18 March,all,morganbritches,"I give XCOM 2 a tentative thumbs up, it reminds me of an annoying kid I played with growing up with and I'll explain why.When I was younger I would play pretend superheoes with a couple of friends and one of them, who we'll call ""Timmy"" for the sake of this review was an only child, whose parents had money and always got him new and shiney stuff. Timmy was kind of spoiled but he had all the best toys, so we tolerated his attitude despite his shortcomings. Whenever we played superheroes each of us would pick a hero you have probably heard of with certain specific and limited powers, for example, I picked Panthero from the Thundercats because he was blue and had nunchuks. There was sort of a gentleman's agreement though, between some of us that this also meant that there were hard counters, so to speak, to our abilities. So, if my other friend, who we'll call ""Mike"" was pretending to be The Human Torch, he would have less strength and agility, but he could shoot fireballs. Creativity and consensus sort of dictated who would win if we battled. The rules were fluid and made up, but there were rules of sorts.Enter Timmy. Timmy would just make s**t up when he was losing. He might be Lion-O and if he got shot with a fireball, he would suddenly decide Lion-O had an ice shield, or he suddenly could shoot lasers back from his eyes and counter the fireballs that way. I remember once, we sort of teamed up on him, because it was the only way to win and he announced he was invincible. There's no counter to that kind of b******t. Did we tolerate it though? Yeah, we got frustrated sometimes, really, really frustrated but he had the cool toys and we did actually like him. So, sometimes we would get really mad and stop playing with him, or go play with someone else but we would eventually come back for more.XCOM 2 is Timmy. You can pretend to be invisible, but Timmy sees you, you can throw a fireball from 10 feet away but Timmy will just declare that you missed. Did you just kill all of Timmy's soldiers? No you didn't b***h, because Timmy just turned the pedestrian next to you in to a giant enemy and suddenly, it's HIS turn and he's going to hit you with his claws that also happen to make the car you are by explode, taking out you and your friends. Thought you showed up all nimbly pimbly on the rooftops, ready to set up the perfect ambush? Well, timmy can see through 4 tinted windows and a skylight and he knows you are there. Is he allowed to do it? Yeah, you agreed to play with him but does it make things immersive and fun? Ehhhh.....I like challenge but not cheese and this game just trololols all over you every chance it gets. Fortunately, there's great modders for it doing great things and the game does provide a solid framework for them to play with. If you aren't super hardcore or don't want any huge setbacks, prepare to savescum and get a mod for it, because it will make you grind your teeth alot."
