,Recommended,268500,24835854,"Posted: 11 August, 2016",all,cosmic cosplayer,"If you played the first game and enjoyed it, you should in theory enjoy this game.Let me explain.The original game had almost no turn counts. This game has quite a few, where you need to compete a mission or complete an objective before the turn counter reaches 0. Not all the stages are like this, as some give you more freedom to camp the spawn like old times. I actually prefer this way better since it forces you to plan even more ahead. making you a better player overall. The game is otherwise almost exactly the same in terms of style, basic game mechanics, and art. Elements like the main map functions are different and more in-depth. Recruiting engineers and scientists is different, you will not be building an item with 150 engineers this time around. These resources are more restricted. This lets you juggle them around strategically between operating a lab or clearing alien debris.I am enjoying this game alot. There are many mods out there in the community to tweak the game however you want. The options are almost endless. I plan to install mods for a 2nd run after completing the main game first."
