,Recommended,268500,20967575,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Rawrcat,"Interesting sequel to an amazing first game. The gameplay has a few improvements which are nice. You don't know if you kill something before you shoot it due to the animation anymore. That was a pretty big annoyance to me, even though it was only a second long animation. You don't have to buy each indivual weapon anymore, but you'll have to buy other equipable items (like medpacs) individually. Buncha other stuff, but it's really nitpicking.The game itself definitely has a new feeling to it. It's not just a rehashed version of XCOM: Enemy Unknown. The world has changed, and so has how you have to play the game. They did a very good job making you feel like you're commanding a rebellion, and I'm enjoying that a lot. The black market is actually a black market... you have to travel to get to it. The immersive aspect of this game is done pretty well.. I've played it for 7 hours straight before I realized it was 4AM. Then my dog got♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥off and I decided to call it quits.There's one big issue for me. I'm running a i7 3.2ghz processor, GTX 770 4Gb, 32Gb of ram and using an SSD to run this game.... which I'm running on medium. There's still a lot of lag on the graphics (and a few other things) ... It's day one, so I'm sure it'll be fixed prompty. Just a little something that irks me. I'd still recommend this game aside from the lag issues because I have faith they'll be fixed pretty quickly.9/10."
