76561197973055218,Not Recommended,268500,20979154,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Fiddlefox,"I'm not sure where to begin with my review of X-Com 2.I want to talk about the lack of refinements over the previous installment, surely. For all its updated looks, tweaks and an alleged degree of polish, X-Com 2 looks and feels remarkably like 'more of the same'.For me, this isn't entirely a good thing.  I loved Enemy Unknown and Within, don't get me wrong, but these installments never felt like the big budget items they are supposed to be.  They always felt more like indie titles: as if they were developed on a shoestring budget.  They were delightful games but rife with bugs and quirks of varying degrees.It seems downright wrong to me that so many of these quirks are still present in the sequel.  It's as if the developers took the core programming of the game and simply ported it over to a new engine, telling themselves ""Yeah, it's good enough eh?""However, what we get is something that feels less like a sequel and more like...  a face lift.  Maybe it is good enough.  It's just hard for me to write a review, forgetting about all the potential I saw in a title and merely judge it on its own merits.Assume for a moment that I can do this however.  How does X-Com 2 stand on its own?Well, pretty okay I guess.   I mean, it's more X-Com right?  X-Com is good, so logically, X-Com 2 must be good as well?  Right?Damn it.  No.  I'm just now wowed.  I'm not impressed.  I keep playing it, but nearly every turn I experience something that puts this bitter taste in my mouth and I just... keep playing XCOM 2 out of some demented sense of obligation.I get so damned angry listening to Bradford and Shen tell me to do things I'm actively trying to accomplish.  I'm so disapointed every time I see a character clip through an object, shoot through one, or float in space.  I'm sick of seeing Stun Lancers forget all about their rifles and launch suicidal melee attacks on my squaddies.  I'm tired of melee attacks in general.  I'm just so heartbroken at the complete lack of attention to detail.I'm sorry.  I can't give it a thumbs up.  I won't.  It just doesn't deserve it.  For any reason."
