,Recommended,268500,21038867,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,Outlaw,"95% sniper chance....miss, grenade enemy at doorway - blows up the wall around target but leaves them unharmed, send in 2 rangers to melee kill and both miss. Enemy trooper repositions and 1 shot kills my ranger with a crit.......Welcome to Xcom 2, the most frustration free gaming experience there is.But seriously this game really has evolved from EU/EW: graphics are much nicer, the AI is smarter and the best improvement in my opinion is the change made to Overwatch. Your troops will take turns at shooting what they see instead of all shooting at once at 1 enemy. Playing as the freedom fighters instead of being an army really makes it feel like every decision you make could impact the future of Xcom and the world as you try to defeat the aliens before the ""doomsday"" clock reaches zero.The RNG system can be a bit odd at times where you will really feel that your troops cant hit a single target but for the most part the hit % is accurate. Changes made to enemy health by adding armour to some of them makes a great positive impact to the game. No longer can you just let your Squadsight snipers obliterate everything in their path as some enemies (mostly robotics) can carry heavy armour that will absorb damage delt to them. Shredding armour or explosives are the way to push forward so I find it now usefull to carry explosives around on missions.There is some stuttering issues I have found which mostly occur after playing it for a couple of hours in one go and that seems to be in the Avenger only. However there are changes that can be made to some of the games files that might remove the stutter issue and sooner or later it will be included in a patch. One thing that I feel the game is missing is no ability to restart the mission from the pause menu; which is something I would like to see added in the future, however just keeping a game save at start of the mission is good enough.Overall Xcom 2 feels like a big step forward over its predesessor with many new features that EU/EW lacked (I am seeing some features that are in the Long War mod however) and I look forward to what the DLC's will add to the game and where the modding community can take it.I recommend this game to anyone who loves Xcom and/or strategy games.10/10"
