create higher chances.. but also means the randomness statistics can not be valid.- when a soldier dies, one or two will get panic and be useless and so most of the time the whole team will be dead.- a sniper at a roof in half-cover cloaked behind a wall, can still be seen and shot dead by one shot- a sniper behind a tree in full-cover is unable to hit an enemy at a line straight through the tree, even though the soldier animation shows he/she is looking around the tree.- an enemy group might detect my movement and get an extra movement turn to hide, which is uneven advantage.- red squares denote tiles that (your soldiers know) are seen by enemies, but moving your soldier will erase some of those (so I have to remember which were red squares for the whole turn).- those red squares do not seem to be updated correctly, as sometimes a square next to it is also seen by the enemy.- in most cases the shown possible movement path excludes red squares, but sometimes they include them.. I have to check closely each time.- the game allows different building types, but only a few are essential and the rest can be discarded as useless.- the same with certain items/weapons, they are not relevant (eg vests cost utility spot but only get you one/two hitpoints)- to do certain actions in the GUI you need to press buttons a lot, while it could have been made eassier/faster with a single button.- very nice animations appear before/after starting missions, however they get bored quickly.. pressing Esc skips them but can also abort starting the mission.- the help inside the game is very bad (eg. choosing between special abilities and building needs many google searches to make them clear).- some missions are impossible- the computer AI's turn and executing of storyline scripting takes a significant amount of time- AI detection is too simply.. when not cloaked the enemy will detecting you when in range (even through high cover)- when still cloaked, the AI guard movement is guided towards you.. making it more difficult to sneak past.So the frustration causes me to:- reload back when one of my soldiers dies or a mission can't be completed ok.- disabling the autosave (which overwrites itself after a few minutes) and manual save before/after each mission.- restart the laptop after each hang.- restarting the game after crash.- hit escape to skip the animations, but not the mission.- keep the amount of actions to a minimum, as there require many mouse movements+clicks.- keep google search open to help me find info about each new selection opportunity."
