76561198040624359,Not Recommended,268500,31415779,Posted: 28 April,all,Absintus,"Verdict: This is game you should ""play"", not a game you should ""buy""... at full price.... here's why:If you're a long time player and fan of Xcom then this game is for you and you will love it, it has some new features and new gameplay mechanics which you will enjoy, but somethings will to some extent put you off and sometimes mad at it.POSITIVE (Minors)Visuals - This game looks amazing, the characters design, the armours, the weapons are superb, plus the customizations makes it even better, huge array of colours and modifications you can do, makes your squads unique.The antagonists (enemies!!!) are also refined and give that extra feel of woe when you are battling them.The maps are smaller (due perhaps to the countdown feature!) and more manageable, they are gorgeous!Gameplay - Its interesting to the least, new moves and weapons, will make you say often: ""wow!!... i can do that!!?"" or ""amazing!"", and when you combine them in Overwatch to set ambushs, the cinematic scene its glorious.The antagonists (enemies!!) are also smarter, they will work to flank you, support their teammates, hoard your squad to a small spot and throw a acid grenade just for 'lols'.They will also flee when they're in a disadvantaged situation and regroup with other far away squads when they're isolated. This nice feature is exarcebated with enemy diversity within the squads, different type of 'aliens' work together to bring the most of pain to your heroes... and they will succeed.Resource management is somewhat easy than previous XCOMs, as the mobile base of yours will be easily upgraded. The missions are enjoyable,challenging and doable...however the difficulty of gameplay will not come from missions, and enemies but rather from some bizarre clusterf**k of things that in my opinion plague this game!Soundtrack - Very nice! Its more moody and paced than the thrilled one of the previous XCOM, it will make you almost cry in those epic moment...i said almost :_(!!NEGATIVE (Majors)Performancea) Pagefile - This game uses at very least 5-6 Gigs of Ram... all fine.. but when you read Pagefile numbers it reaches 6-7 Gigs of Pagefile!!!!... In 2016!!?  For a total of 13 Gigs of RAM + Pagefile!! ?? If it runs on a lot of Pagefile it can only mean one thing: Stutter!! Horrid gamebreaker stutter!! And if you put mods  it can reach higher.b) Stutter, cutscenes - This game has a huge enjoyable cutscenes, when your squad drop from the transport in AO (Area of Operation) in zip lines, that is so awesome... until stutter happens!Not only in in-game cutscenes but also in the plot cutscenes, which are excepcionally well made and one of the best parts of this game, but are dragged to the ground with stutter and small pauses! And it kills it!c) Anti-aliasing - MSAA its a no-no, FXAA will help, but all AA in XCOM2 will drag your FPS to the 24-34 fps, VRAM even with 3.4 Gigs of use in its peak, does not seem to include AA... probably its all in Pagefile! The rest of graphics option seem ok!Gameplaya) Battle difficulty - The Devs right before launch thought the game was easy, so they made it more harder (not my words, google it!!), what resulted instead was a cringy set of combat never seen in XCOM.The Missions themselves are not hard, BUT, the AI just for some reason overwhelms you with sheer numbers, and more often it pulls the heavy-hitters, that in some point later in the game its Gatekeepers, Sectopods and Andromedons in all missions!From the simple beacon hack to the UFO 'break-in' raid... and early you just thought Codexes ( an antagonist...) were hard!The Last Mission its absurd: you have to deal with the bosses, and... you guessed... a huge sea of enemies, which comes with all with the above mentioned... and more!There was a beacon mission, when you have to run to it at the same time the enemies are going to it and destroy it. The AI distopic sense of gameplay balance there, just went up the charts, i have never seen such battle and it was soo cheesy, that that one beats the last mission on the matter of difficulty.b) Can see enemies & shoot through walls - Another constant 'feature' its the shooting through the walls, and the cheating spotting of adversaries through them, by the heroes and enemies alike.c) Super powerful squads at later stages -  the easiness wich you can reach full unstoppable power with your squads is a feature that i have mix opinions. You can enjoy the new armour and weaponary and its uses, but when at the same you can dispatch 5-6 enemies with at least a heavy hitter, in a ambush with Overwatchits laughable, Grenadiers, Rangers and the Super Cheesy Gunslinger Build of Sharpshooter, takes some of the tactical aspect of the game.But then you say:""... but you said the AI was also cheesy, so it compensates!"", and you're right, but what happens next it that the AI compensates cheesiness over chessiness, and it bring more and more enemies, so in reality your advantage its lost.You can see that, when in the last mission, one of your fully upgraded to an 'unstoppable-tank' Grenadier, gets overwhelmed by an absurd 3-4 fully upgraded advent basic troops plus 2 Heavy-Hitters! Thats the only way to kill him!Even when you, prior to a mission, made a mission where you stopped enemy reinforcements for a while, i saw the AI pull reinforcements anyway! Wassup wit dat!!?d) Lack of menus and of informative details - The game lack proper menus, for squad built and rooms management as well as shortcuts buttons to take were you want to go. You want to go a menu you have to click, click, click!You have to manually, remove items, armours from each squad members in order to reuse them on other squad members.Avatar countdown is also somewhat lacking, Comm Rooms and Towers and some of the most critical investments, but it doesnt get enfasized! I manage to pull myself of a predictament (lack of intel, and cost of Contacts), due to a hasty set of missions!CONCLUSION (post verdict!)Game seems rushed (the lack of menu interfaces show that and the poor perfomance) and its mainly a ruffed console port, you have to use tweaks to repair things Devs should had made themselves.When you have to:1) Limit the framerate to 30fps to reduce stutter on a PC.2) Enable Pagefile to large amounts (terrible on SSD's, altough Windows still needs some pagefile even on SSD), and some people dont want to enable/have pagefile on their systems.3) Use Mods to help the menus and item allocation, because the way i see it mods should enrich the game, not fix it. The  'Inventory Use mod' plus the 'Uniform Manager' were critical to improve the gameplay, plus other mods while not relevant to the game helps it with new uniforms and camos for example.It Crashes, Stutters, bots glitch sometimes like hitting twice in a turn.The 'Your PC is weak and you need to upgrade' doesnt cut it anymore, and companies need to pay more atention to this.Like i said if you like XCOM, XCOM2 will give good moments,especially if everything runs smooth.In the final mission (Commander Difficulty) i lost my Blade Master Ranger and self-based Bad-A*s Grenadier, in a epic last moment, swathing through enemies with blade,shotgun, grenades and heavy-gun (The pile of bodies was huge!!), just so their teammates could do that last assault on the boss and save the day!Performance more than anything its the culprit of a not recommendation, when you ask 60 coins for a game, you have to deliver the 60 Dollars/Euros product.I cant recommend a game when its broken. There was 99% to make this game a Hit, with a Critical and it missed... thats NOT XCOM. Positive recommendation means to the game works during gaming, and on your PC, remember that PC gave fame and to some degree support to XCOM, not consoles.Buy it on sale.Edited* for Errors & Text Consistency ( darn Sectoids!)"
