76561198026873914,Recommended,268500,21783877,"Posted: 12 March, 2016",all,Ghouleh,"It's a lukewarm 'Yes'.PROS-Reworked classes feel a lot more well-rounded.-Psi Operatives can be researched sooner, and have a lot more options at their disposal.-Aesthethically pleasing in it's environments.-New world map feels more dynamic than the Enemy Unknown's.-Characters have a bit more personality to them, including your own silent, invisible protagonist.-New Concealment mechanic adds a new, welcome layer of strategy to the game.-Modding support is going to be the lifeblood of the game going forward, and I cannot overstate how much this is an excellent decision that's going to extend the game's lifespan considerably.TRADE-OFFS-Base-building is streamlined and simplified-Almost all missions are timed; makes for riveting gameplay at times. At other times it's just annoying.-Whilst cosmetic customization seems to have become more in-depth, it seems to have come at the cost of helmets that don't look dumb.-New Credits/Intel/Power/Contacts resource dynamic changes up how you go about things.-Tech Tree has been reworked to separate technology upgrades (which are global once purchased) from unique randomized items (which have to be built one by one)-Plot is just as badly explained as Enemy Unknown's.CONS-Badly optimized. Stuttering, freezes, long loading times, crashes and corrupted save files.-No fighter jet strategic allocation or combat.-No independent robot characters, such as SHIVs.-No MELD-related technologies. Yet.-Hacking seems to have been poorly thought out and is rarely worth the trouble, since it's statistically disadvantageous across the board to ever use it.-No capturing live aliens. Skulljacking is nowhere as fun, challenging or useful as capturing live aliens.-""Shaken"" mechanic is a needless penalty that will annoy you till death.Keeping it short: I loved Enemy Unkwnown, but XCOM 2 feels a bit too samey for my tastes, even though it's a good game in it's own right. If you're up for more of the same, go for it. If I had known all that I know now, I wouldn't have picked it up for full price, at least not until they fixed most of the optimization issues and spawned a couple dozen good mods."
