76561198054187425,Recommended,268500,20991391,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Dasta,"Spent the first 4 hours making soldiers and changing little details until they're perfect. Like the Sims. With Guns. Then they all died. Like the Sims.11/10 would Sims again.Seriously though. I've had a blast playing this game, it's been fantastic. I know a lot of people are reporting the optimization is poor, but for the first time ever, I'm not one of them. I have all settings at max except for Anti-Aliasing which is set to FXAA. No frame drops, not even with grenade overlays where TotalBiscuit reported his frame drops. I guess I got lucky.Definitely some bugs, but fortunately none of them have been game breaking. A little bit of polish will clean those up with a patch, soon I hope.I love the timers, even though I was worried I'd hate them. They force me to move faster. I can't overwatch camp for 30 minutes and win, I actually have to be active, take risks, be aggressive. And I find myself enjoying the game more when I get down to 2 or 3 turns left and I need to mad dash it to evac but a drop ship is coming in. It's like a movie, slower start ramping up into an intense finish where you're on the edge of your seat.I'm a mixture of happy and sad with the base building. Happy, cause I suck at basebuilding. It's my greatest weakness, I always overthink it and shoot myself in the foot. But sad, because it's a nobrainer now. It's a matter of time and resources, not planning.The tech tree pacing feels off too, but it may be because I delayed the Black Site for so long, so I got Mag weapons really fast. I feel like I missed out on conventional weapons missions and shot past into midgame too early for the full experience. I'll have to check it out when I play it again, blacksite sooner and see if the tech pacing feels better.TL;DRThe game isn't perfect, there's lots of polish to be done still, and hopefully the DLC in Spring/Summer will give more depth. But it's still an amazing game, and I would recommend it in a heartbeat. I'm having too much fun sharing stories with my friends about crazy stuff as it happens. It's a blast.8/10"
76561197982087969,Recommended,268500,21039138,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,Richard,If you liked the first one then I can recommend this game. There is a lot more added to the game and it plays a lot faster and more aggressive than the first one which I feel has addressed some of the pacing issues the first one had. This time around it feels like every encounter is make or break and having completed the game on normal ironman I can say that there were times I was really at the brink and cursing the game.It does have a lot of performance and bug issues but I’m playing on low detail with speedfan and it mostly works fine. Some complaints I have read involve the use of timers or difficult enemies. There are already workshop mods to remove/extend most mission timers (personally they offer challenge) and as for the enemies they aren’t so bad once you figure out how to counter them using armor piercing abilities etc.Your soldiers are also going to die a lot and you will probably fail or have to bail on some missions but it’s to be expected. I put over 300 hours into the first game and I lost my first two campaigns in this one.Overall I can’t excuse the performance/bugs but they should get fixed and I will probably say that I think you need to play the first one to enjoy this one. It doesn’t feel very beginner friendly and is somewhat overwhelming with the random nature the campaign tends to have now. The training wheels come off fast in this game so playing the first one is a personal recommendation (plus it’s usually pretty cheap on steam).There’s a lot of story and replay value to this game and I did enjoy it so I’d give it 10/10 any day but maybe I’m just a biased fan or a compulsive gambler…Additional: The DLC plans look interesting and the teaser at the end is just great.
