,Recommended,268500,20983947,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,smartbombradio,"The game is a lot of fun so far; however it needs fine tuning and optimization. Turn limits aren't awful but should all be extended about 2 - 3 turns - it's not so much that they break the game as the very short limits stop you from experimenting with tactics and play styles. It's MOVE MOVE MOVE GO GO GO because you've got a time limit (or you have to help unreasonably stupid humans survive - they seem to be able to run and hide from me, but have trouble running and hiding when I'm trying to keep them safe/supposed to save a certain number.) So yeah this needs play balancing and like 2 performance patches and that needs to be said up front.That being said, the game is really fun when it works - in many/most ways improved or an equally good but different experience over the original, so far. Story is interesting, missions are mostly pretty fun, the new enemies are punishing, and the settings are pretty cool. Character customization is interesting and varied, both asthetically and choosing their abilities. Stealth allows some really cinematic ambushes.When this game works it's amazingly fun, so I hope the devs are patching it up/finding some sort of compromise on the timer because I'd play this, and mods using this general system, for quite some time.That's all I've done so far so that's all I can speak on, but it's an enthusiastic thumbs up, with a qualifier that I'm assuming the devs will take some serious runs at the optimization, enemy AI, Civillian AI when you're protecting them, and extending the clock (or eliminating it all together, but I don't think it's terrible I just think they need to loosen the belt a few notches to allow a few tactics other than forward blitz.)(Update: Trying game with a Mod that minimizes the number of missions with timers. Much improved.)"
