,Recommended,268500,21004922,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Ishmael,"I recommend this game fairly strongly. I'm enjoying the game a lot, the story is better, the core gameplay feel like ""Enemy Within, but better"", and overall I'm having a blast. However, I am going to list a few things that irk me and may irk some people looking to buy. Basically, I'm saying ""I recommend this game unless any of the following deeply bother you.""1. Performance issues abound. Turning off AA and AO kill off most of the performance issues for me, and allows me to run the game are max settings at a pretty decent FPS most of the time. However, there is severe FPS drops during common cutscences (Skyranger landing and taking off) as well as moving from room to room on the base. This is pretty unfortunate, and I hope this is ironed out soon as I think this is the game's most pressing issue.2. Mission timers. Mission timers are surprisingly divisive. In my opinion, the mission timers works with one of the reoccuring themes of the game, which is ""time is a resource"". The tried and true method of crawling across the map slowly in overwatch still works in some missions, but now there are more trade-offs between going slow and going fast. With that said, mission timers could be improved. I feel like some missions begin a countdown before what I consider reasonable. If the aliens discover there's a hack, or there's a broken down convoy, then I understand the countdown.But what about a mission where you have to extract a VIP and Advent doesn't know you're coming? Or missions where you have to kidnap a dark VIP that, again, the Advent don't know you're coming for? I feel like these countdowns shouldn't begin until concealment is broken. Otherwise though, I don't have a problem with mission timers. For anyone that does though, there is a mod that increases mission timers and another one that gets rid of them altogether.3. [MINOR ISSUE ALERT] Lower face props like the striped bandana should match your soldier's color scheme better. This is so minor that I'm only putting it here in the off chance that a developer read this and tweaks it so bandanas match your soldiers' color schemes.4. [MINOR ISSUE ALERT] No Second Wave options? But what about my marathon? :(5. Camera is garbage. If there is one mod besides SMGs that I wholeheartedly recommend, it is the one that improves the camera so you can look at the battlefield from more than four angles.Overall, I recommend the game (which is what Steam is asking for in these reviews by the way people). If you want to get a better impression, I strongly recommend TotalBiscuit's ""WTF is XCOM 2?"" on Youtube."
