,Recommended,268500,20983138,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,Jont,"At last i have closed down the game. I managed to get stuck so after about 14 hours divided into two play sessions i've been able to take a break. I'll be making some points about the positive and negative things i've encountered thus far.Positive:- Intense & timecramped missions that make you plan out every single round and a system that really punishes you for not doing so. The satisfaction after barely making it out alive is amazing and it really fits the theme of the game.- The anthill type basebuilding aswell as the construction and research system is rewarding and satisfying while staying true to the previous XCOM titles.- The map where you plan all of your operations and setup links between the different parts of the world is greatly worked upon compared to the other titles in the way that it's alot more interactive and brings in a bunch of new, sweet features.- Great character customization that allows for pimping out your favorite soldiers, some of the options are a little more limited than the others but it's not a big deal. You can also save your characters so that you may encounter identical ones in other playthroughs.Negative:- I am playing on medium but the textures are still pretty horrible at times for being a 2016 game, i know strategy games aren't supposed to excel in graphics but it does annoy me at times.- The camera angels are NOT good. For a game that has so many mini-cutscenes and camera angles all over the place they are incredibly bad at times to the point where the I'm looking at the floor, roof or wherever instead of where the action is going on.- Optimization is pretty bad at the moment, im getting FPS drops at medium settings from time to time and i feel as if i really shouldn't be getting them at medium settings seeing as i can play etc. The Witcher 3 on high graphics with almost constant 50+ FPS on a GTX 960.Overall it's still a great game and im sure that most of these issues will be fixed within the first few months and the things that don't get improved upon will certainly be modded in. Also, if you don't enjoy RNG and punishing gameplay then you might want to reconsider purchasing this game.8/10 PRETTY GOOD"
