76561197963638786,Not Recommended,268500,21147218,"Posted: 12 February, 2016",all,Kyzar,"I'm a bit dissapointed with XCOM2 so far, have to say.I come to XCOM having played Laser Sqad in the 80's, then the Original UFO, then XCOM. XCOM and Enemy Within sacrifice a *lot* of the micromanagement for a more accessible and fantastically entertaining turn-based game. Still a long way from perfect, but I have maybe a couple of hundred hours in XCOM / EW - one of my top 3 games ever.XCOM2 has a lot going for it. It is MUCH harder (thankfully). New (and the welcome return of old) aliens, great maps, the rebel mechanic seems interesting and the ambush idea is probably superb. I say probably because almost every mission has a turn limit - which seems a wierd juxtaposition to 'take your time and be sneaky sneaky' new tools. How can I set up a great ambush, reach the objective on the other side of the map and get back to the exit in 8 turns? It makes no sense at all and is very frustrating. I can't develop a play style and learn the nuances of a squad whene everything is done on a sprint. I've had one map so far (a Blacksite) which wasn't time-based and it was superb - but only one. And now I have the avatar project counting up on the geoscape, so I don't feel I can explore the world either.I realise that modern gaming is all about instant gratification and I'm an ancient 40 year old who likes 'the good old days' - but honestly XCOM was superb in being almost alone in bringing a more thoughtful pace of play and probably thanks to that we have rising popularity of the more faithful UFO clones out there, which I'll be getting into more. We wrinklies have disposable income as well - it's not all wasted on providing games for our grunting, twitching, sleep and daylight deprived offspring :o) I just wish there was a game with the visual appeal, AI, enemies and interface of XCOM2 with at least the depth and freedom of XCOM/EW.Would be great if there was a third thumb on the rating system - not recommending sounds harsh (if you like being under endless overly-contrived countdowns and want maps as quick as a round of CS:GO, this is the game for you), but I can't really recommend it either - can we get a 'meh' thumb? :o)"
