,Recommended,268500,20998649,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Sunzo,"I'm loving this game.It has what I loved in X-Com: EU and EW with new features/enemies/developments sprinkled in.It's an absorbing strategy with diverse enough character customisation for units to feel unique, on the subject of customisation there's a lot more to it than there was in the previous installments, so if you enjoy having your own unit, you'll love customising in this game.The new enemy units are both really cool and terrifying, every time I see a new enemy unit, I make sure it dies as soon as possible rather than seeing what it can do. (and then later on it catches me with my pants down on another mission because my veteran's are all recovering)I could sing this game's praises for days so lets get to what I think is wrong with it.The game is incredibly more difficult, now this is both a good point and a bad point.It's only a bad point because of the next things I'm going to discuss.+There is a game loading bias. Shots I've made before loading have hit and have gotten criticals, then after loading, they miss entirely, and after many consequetive loads, each time it fails to even hit.it seems every first shot after loading a game seems to have a drastic aim hit, I've even tested this out by making the exact same shot in the exact same place with the enemy at the exact same health and in the exact same spot before: both with the unit in question firing first, and with another unit firing before hand then firing with the unit in question.In the latter example the other unit shoots, misses and the unit in question then fires, hits, GG game over.in the first example the unit in question misses the target and another unit has to attempt to hit them.This balant ""Anti-Save Scum System"" is insanely annoying and with the increased difficulty of this installment means I've spent a great deal of time having to wrestle with it, something I do not find fun and really detracts from the experience.+Long War influences: The game is definitely harder, feeling more like Long War than the actual base games EU and EW.This is both a good and a bad thing too, only being a bad thing simply because of the Anti-Save Scum System.+Caters to Hardcore gamers: There's no good and bad to this one in my opinion, those who prefer hardcore gameplay will see this as a huge plus, but for those who seem themselves more as casuals, or inbetween the two (like myself) will find this to be a particular feature that one has to take with some salt, water and lots of sessions crying because I lost my favourite sharp shooter and STOP MAKING ME RELOAD TO SAVE HER FOR ♥♥♥♥ SAKEThe game is also host to some really annoying bugs and glitches, after experiencing them first hand, I can see why they were exclusively a negative point in the IGN review.as they stand, they are not game breaking but really detract from the experience, and end up only being funny the first time or if you're really easily amused (or high off your face)I love this game, and I'm definitely slapping it with a 9/10When some patches get released and those bugs get fixed, it'll raise to a 9.5/10 and if a second wave option is added, or a patch is released to fix the Anti-Save Scum System, it'll definitely get a 10/10 from me.(Disclaimer: many may see the Anti-Save Scum System as something that's not so bad, and may want to dismiss my opinion on it, but before you do, please look at it from this perspective: someone who is going to save scum, say to save their favourite unit, is going to save scum over and over and over until they get the result they want, having to put up with continuous loading over the course of an hour replaying a single turn to try and get that PERFECT scenario where everyone lives, is insanely painful and boring and really detracts from this excellent game)"
