ve to know how to work with what you got, unless you like to be a whimp and save scum your every failed shot. It's in this games' blood, that's the point. ""OMG i can't finish mission in 8 turns :^((("" - WTF?Game is fairly balanced on Classic so far, except for annual major diff spikes here and there, there's nothing that human being with three digit iq couldn't handle. Certain class abilities can even be called absolutely OP and can pull your whole squad through completely doomed operation.If anything, everything is much easier than originals, where you can't scratch your bum without throwing smoke grenade first.There are also people who are STILL complaining that it's nothing like original UFO defense, but they are old farts by now, they can complain all they want.As for the changes from previous games since reboot - i like almost every change in mechanics. EVERYTHING is handled better. Tactical combat is much more compelling, geoscape gameplay makes much more sense, base management is somewhat nonexistent, but i don't really care that much. To be fair, this thing about single base was stupid in the first place, so making mobile base is pretty much right decision, considering that introducing multiple bases would only spawn more ""too difficult >:("" whine at this point. I wish there was more variety in weapons between tiers, but that's what mods are for. Full mod support, baby!Majorly improved story, A E S T H E T I C S, sound, graphics, gameplay, a lot of cool science-fiction stuff here and there, snakes with boobs, CODEX'S BOOTY, ability to create a squad with Hatsune Miku and Samuel L. Jackson because of pretty rad customization options, what the hell more do you want? Core mechanics of previous game aren't really changed, so if you didn't like them back then - you won't like this one. But with whole gorilla warfare theme everything sort of makes much more sense, so you still can try it even if you didn't like Enemy Unknown/WithinAs someone who's following franchise since the original games, i can say that this game is best effort to bring XCOM into modern pc game reality without just copypasting outdated mechanics to pander to hardcore oldfarts who can just go and play the originals for 100th time.  It's basically like Heroes 5 compared to Heroes 3, both are excellent games with the same spirit, one is just much more modern, so it will lose a lot of charm for MLG-LAN-PARTY-RANDOM-MAP-PROS.I give this game 100 hidden movements out of 100 and encourage you to buy and play it as soon as possible. But if you are man of faint heart and crаppy rig - wait for more performance patches and gameplay mods."
