othing.-classical XCOM BS shots. Having a soldier target a mob through a wall, through line of sight behind a pillar, aim at the camera and shoot BACKWARDS behind them.-doors don't work completely. Instead of opening or being kicked down, mobs will just run through the doors. I've even had mobs aggro through sealed doors/walls even though my soldiers don't have line of sight of them immediately.The game seems badly optimized too. I'm not sure if its because I'm still running win7 or what, but I had my computer custom-made to handle high-graphics games on max settings, and when I tried to put XCOM on ultra, my framerate was like .01fps. I had to go back to the default medium setting.None of this, however, is keeping me from enjoying the game. I have to force myself to stop playing so I can eat/sleep/work, and each mission always has me wanting more. I do get very annoyed when you're scanning and you get a priority council mission 1 day from finishing a relay, and I've noticed the world map seems to stick sometimes, like not letting you switch to missions and yanking your cursor back to the Avatar counter. It frustrates me too that dialogue gets cut off. In XCOM EU, npcs would continue talking even if you switched locations until they finished saying their particular segment, but in X2 I missed several lines of interesting dialogue because the npc will start talking just as I swap over to another room then the sentence gets cut off.It's definately worth buying regardless, just needs additional polishing. Hopefully a optimization or tweak patch somewhere down the line."
