,Recommended,268500,21021199,"Posted: 7 February, 2016",all,junkevil,"Performance wise, I was having some choppy fps here and there until I changed the AA from MSAA to FXAA. It's been smooth and solid ever since. I have everything else set to max and am running it on a GTX 960 w/ 4gb of ram.Gameplay wise, It's a fantastic sequel to Enemy Unknown. If you enjoyed the previous entry in the Xcom series, and are looking for a challenge, here it is. In the previous game players would delay doing certain things so they could have more time do research and build up their squads. That's no longer an option, Sitting still and doing nothing will ensure failure.On top of that, the enemies have all evolved. Sectoids have been spliced with humans and now have more HP and psionic abilities, Thin Men are now snakes that can grab you from across the map and slowly squeeze the life out of you, Chrysallids have more HP, are armored, move faster, and poison you with one hit.  You know what that poison does? makes your people turn into a giant pod that spawns more Chrsyallids.The skill trees have changed a bit too, but for the most part it's the same. Rangers, formerly assault now carry swords and can dash across the map and cut people down. they start with this instead of run and gun, but you can get run and gun later in addition. Feels very similar anyways. Weapon mods like scopes are permanently added to guns, and can't be shared or removed, only replaced.In conclusion I would recommend this game to anyone who likes tactical turn based games. I'd highly recommend it to people who liked the previous game."
