76561198008018101,Not Recommended,268500,29464223,Posted: 24 January,all,MMXI,"Pros :+Steam workshop gives it almost infinite customisability (from cosmetics to gameplay).+Aesthetics (Purely subjective, good if you're into the near future sci-fi look).+The concealment mechanic genuinely changes up the gameplay from the first game. You really do feel like a guerilla force fighting an established enemy.+Good audio design (Again subject to personal taste). The guns sound like they have some real force behind them and the sound track really nails the atmosphere.+Combat mechanics have some real variety to them compared to the first game. Mech enemies can be hacked and disabled. Psi soldiers can manipulate the enemy. Lots of utility items.Cons:-Lack of control. The game really likes to shove cutscenes and combat animations in your face. Camera control is constantly being taken away from you to show you the mission objective, alerted enemies or basically anything except movement. Really breaks up the pacing. The game was only bearable for me with the ""Stop wasting my time"" mod.-Paid cosmetic DLCs. Really seems redundant and a waste of development time to sell cosmetics when the steam workshop exists.-The turn timers really take away a lot of your tactical options. Half the missions have tight turn timers meaning you have no choice but to rush the objective or fail the missions, no time to scout the area or set up for ambushes. Fixable with mods but still deserves a mention.-The UI is really iffy. It might have been a personal problem but it seemed like you had to get your cursor on a certain pixel to even get a grenade to land where you wanted it. At times I would tell a soldier to move to a certain square but then the cursor would suddenly flip to the adjacent square and it would be a wasted turn.I just couldn't get into the game no matter how much I want to. I have started maybe 30+ games, played less than 5 past the first couple of hours and finished it twice. I really wanted to like the game but just couldn't get past the design choices.My main problem was just the lack of pacing. It was impossible to really get immersed into a missions when the game was constantly telling you ""look at this cool thing!"", ""look at these guys over here!"", ""look at this mission objective while Bradford gives you a long monologue!"". Even mods coudln't fully fix this problem. I understand that the developers spent hundreds of man hours crafting a more cinematic experience but really it could have done with an option to turn the animations and story VO off, especially when you're on the nth playthrough.This problem is even more exacerbated on the enemies' turn. Games like Endless Legend give you option to increase combat animation speed. An option to increase enemy turn animation speed by like 8x would be amazaing. Sometimes it's really cool to see your fully customised solider blow the brains(CPUs?) out of a sectopod with a plasma cannon, just not every turn. It just felt like less than half the time you played the game you had any actual input.This is purely subjective as well, but I really did not like the way the pod spawns worked. The tactics felt more like something out of an MMO where you would try and ""Pull"" one pack of mobs at a time or risk getting overwhelmed. It really limited your movement options and made the maps feel small and cramped.In a turn based tactics game the design philosphy seems to have been to make you play the game a certain instead of giving the player more freedom to complete objectives creatively.It's a real shame that I just could not enojy the game with some of the core design choices involved. These are things that cannot easily be fixed with mods either.This is only my opinion but I just couldn't recommend the game as it is."
76561197972921451,Not Recommended,268500,33612180,Posted: 17 July,all,<|☥|Inesophet|☥|>,"I really really Tried to like it. I loved the first game, what a fresh breeze of air. This one however ( and i will get alot of flak from fanboys for this) is not good. The Presentation is breathtaking. Super epic Music intros and all manner of awesomeness. Great Voiceacting and so on.However you deserve to know why you may not like this one. Xcom is a Tactics game. It lives and breathes from being 70% Tactics, 20% Strategy and 10% luck. Xcom2 is 70% luck as far as i experienced it. Because of a few mechanics, most missions have a pretty brutal Timelimit. You either need to cross the whole map to reach a certain point, or rescue somebody, or rescue alot of people. You have around 3-8 turns time for this. That means the game forces you to rush. I personally hate this in tactics game. You cant set up a propper ambush. And more often then not you end up with your pants down running in a group of Aliens. Ok RELOAD.Now you know where the aliens are, advance until then. Take them out. Oh Soldier 1 Missed. Soldier 2...he missed aswell. Soldier 3... 2 Damage! Enemy proceeds killing the Squads. RELOAD!Ok this time Soldier 1 Hits. Yay, enemy dead. Soldier 2...missed. Soldier 3...missed again. Enemy kills soldier 3, Soldier 1 is panicked. RELOAD (spoiler...next turn everybody is dead)When you finally get to the terminal (after MANY reloads), Oh reinforcments are coming and dropping in the flank of my squad. Sucks to be me i guess. Squad dead. RELOADNow i know that reinforcements are coming, Get to the terminal, Have everybody in position. Reinforcments now arrive at a different place. (again flanked) Squad Dead. RELOADAfter countless reloads the mission is completed.Im sorry but this is NOT fun. Its bl00dy frustrating.Another big problem is that enemies can more often then not shoot through walls. Also once you are spotted the enemy ALWAYS knows your position even if you are not in its line of sight. So outflanking an enemy, or trying to be sneaky doesnt work. Why the timelimit on the missions? I dont get it. Anyway if you look for a good Tactics game and you liked the First Xcom, get yourself Jagged Alliance 2 it is still today unsurpassed in quality. If thats a bit too old, try Silent Storm. Also a Brilliant Tactics game.However if the afromentioned scenario and type of gameplay doesnt bother you, go for it."
