76561198071012471,Recommended,268500,21069801,"Posted: 8 February, 2016",all,nikoglis,"After a long wait, XCOM 2 is out, to grab us by the balls once again, whip our backs, and command us to call it Mama Susie. This is not an easy game. This is not a fun game. Not for the uninitiated to the ways of the XCOM. You will feel hype, enthusiasm as you hit your first shot, you will curse at your buddy Billy that you named your best soldier after, because he missed a 95% shot. GET YOUR♥♥♥♥♥♥TOGETHER BILLY.You will feel the excitement when you finally get that ♥♥♥♥♥ mission that you were stuck on for hours, immense satisfaction when you finally kill that mo$^£$%""£ piece of $""$%""%&^ c*cksucking codex that keeps teleporting around the map and clones itself, and it just WON'T ♥♥♥♥ING DIE.You will feel your balls shrinking up as the aliens almost complete the avatar project, and you only have 20 days to stop them, and the eventual relief when you barely manage to achieve that 4 days before you lose, OR the pity for yourself when you do lose and you have to start all over again.If i could describe this game in 3 words i would say :Uphill battle simulator.Improvements from xcom 2 and general pros:-Much wider mission variety.-Many more and deeper customization options. You can even give them cigars now.-Late game is harder now. In fact, i lost one of my campaigns, even though it had reached late game.-Classes are much more diverse than before, and every class is useful, with it's own merits. You will see what i mean, when you enter a hard mission and you don't have a specific class with you, and how you will feel it's skills missing from your arsenal deeply affects you.-A new loot system is in the game, that lets you individually upgrade your weapons, which you LOSE if the soldier carrying them dies on the field and you don't extract his dead corpse.-Also, the effect of ""billy panics, and shoots his friends dead"" is much less prevelant than before, althought this might just be on the default difficulty. I imagine things get much tougher later on.Pros or cons: (depending on your point of view)-The game has the whole mentality of ""Even if you do everything perfectly, you can still lose"", and it's obvious in this game. You WILL get shot from half way across the map, you WILL lose your best sniper from a random crit that came out of nowhere, and  you WILL get shased down by ufos when you least expect it. This aspect, everyone can take it on a different light, but you have been warned.Cons:-New players to xcom will feel lost. If you don't know what xcom is, i recommend to get xcom enemy unknown first, as it is a smoother transition and will explain much of the mechanics of this game. I guess firaxis thought that the only people that will buy this game are players who already know about xcom, but still, i feel it's a misfire on their part-Hacking is in the game now, but i feel like more could be done with it. You can hack robots, towers, and some objectives, and that's pretty much it. It also follows the same mechanic, so be prepared for your friend Tommy to ♥♥♥♥ up his hacking with 90% chance of success, and suddenly you have a super mech chasing after you.-Several performance issues, either minor either major. For me personally, the game suffered from some framedrops after a lot of hours of playing, and it can't really handle alt tabbing that well. Some visual bugs, and also only 1 heavy crash (again due to alt tabbing), but thankfully, there is a new autosave function now, so use that.In conclusion:If you are familiar to xcom and you love a good challenge (and you are also a masochist) you will love this game. Be prepared to lose friends, family, your dog, your 3rd cousin from your mothers side. This is a tough game, and even harder in higher difficulty levels. Recommended ONLY for those that know what's coming to them.Right now, with the minor performance issues, it's an 9/10 for me. Once patches are introduced and further customization is implemented, it's a clean 10/10."
