e by one.Flush the balance down the toilet. Did Josh Sawyer work on XCom2?The game, unlike the first one, is made stressful too much.Some will defend countdowns, I just can't. Sure, I managed to finish all missions in time, but instead of relaxing and thinking about the best strategy, I'm constantly playing bull-through-the-wall. It's rediculous. And it's not just one mission, seems to me that half of them are timebased. It's a design fail and I've just installed timers disabled mod.The stress doesn't stop there. Some Avatar Project aliens launched and is in progress. You're constantly notified that if you don't react… And instead of contacting resistance, dealing with other threats (there are so called dark events that boost aliens if you don't react), getting intel and ressources, you're pressed into destroying alien facilities ""otherwise something very bad will happen"". Well shove off! I have enough of stress at my job with deadlines, so I've found another ""mod"" how to stop avatar crap from progress and installed that too.Percentages on shooting seem to work correctly, you'll hit most of times if it's 70% or above, miss almost always if it's lower than 40%.But on hacking? You hack a street scanner which drops will of all mobs. Then attempt to hack the biggest robot you've seen in the game so far. Your (unit's) hack skill is 100 and robot's is 80. You have a chance to succeed 80%. And you fail each and every time!One of your soldiers got shot. 3HP down. Another one too. 5HP down. You did the mission, returned.The one who suffered 5HP is barely wounded and has to recover for 3 days. The one who got scratched and lost 3HP is gravely wounded and has to spend 14 days recovering! What's even worse if you reload autosave prior to mission end and finish it again, wounds and recovery time can change for better or for worse!What kind of stupid design this is?Mods to the rescue… Just installed ""Its Just A Scratch"" that stops at least wounds being roguelike.That'd be bad parts.A good part? It's fun! And god help me, it's addictive. It's one of those ""I need to go to sleep, lemme do just another mission"" and after that ""okay, one more"".This is one of those games that could have been a masterpiece in right hands, but due to many design fails will be remembered as utterly flawed gem.If it's still on sale (deluxe edition, whih is complete edition was 45% off) buy it, you won't feel sorry.Now lemme return to it so I see which new ""boss"" the game will drop on my underdeveloped soldiers."
