76561198006187879,Recommended,268500,21971382,"Posted: 21 March, 2016",all,ROW ROW,"Just finished it. Loved it. It's a freaking X-COM. Improved and better. See aliens - kill aliens. Good luck, Commanders."
,Recommended,268500,22003623,"Posted: 23 March, 2016",all,Docta McNasty,"XCOM 2 builds upon the idea that you failed miserably in XCOM: Enemy Unknown. And that is a damn good thing.Where to start... Well, the concept of having a mobile base is very good, as you actually feel like you're on the run from the alien overlords and their grizzly genetically-altered army. You need to collect resources in order to survive, and the different things you can discover while searching are pretty standard, but varied enough for them to fit perfectly. The only thing about this is that early on you can get overwhelmed with the amount of areas you need to search, which can lead to a slow start that gives the aliens an early advantage.The soldier customization puts most RPGs to shame and is easily the best part of the game. With the extensive modding community it is possible to create nearly any soldier you can think of. What other game can you have Halo's Spartans and the crew of Mass Effect's Normandy fighting side by side while the Gears of War decimate the aliens?The combat feels mostly the same as it did in XCOM: EU, but with a twist. The new concealed mechanic allows you to ambush first. But you need to be careful as you can end up getting ambushed yourself if you get overconfident. I think my only gripe with this mechanic is that you can run into enemies in the most bull****y spots, and it can ultimately screw you over for the rest of the mission. Luckily if you're like me, you'll end up saving scum and reloading. Fortunately you won't have to sit through the aliens murdering your soldiers over and over like with Enemy Unknown. You can reload a save during their go at you. That said, where is the Restart Mission button?Storywise, for my first playthrough I was intrigued with the way it was going. I liked the reveals, the twists, and the lore all the way through and it genuinely felt like the aliens were playing humanity like a flute. (damn you Speaker!) That said, the ending kind've feels the same as with Enemy Unknown in that it feels so ubrupt.Ultimately, if you're a fan of the series, you'll love this game. If you're new to the series, you'll love this game. It's the best of the series and with the extensive modding community it's only going to get better."
