,Recommended,268500,21356161,"Posted: 20 February, 2016",all,Afflatus,"XCOM: Enemy Unknown and its expansion Enemy Within successfully captured the old-school vibe of one of PC gaming's iconic turn-based strategies for a modern marketplace. XCOM 2 continues this trend, and provides everything you'd expect from a sequel to one of the greatest strategy games of all time.The premise of the XCOM series is simple: aliens are taking over the world, and it's up to you to lead mankind's resistance. Develop your troops, outfit them with stolen technology, and deploy them in strategic locations across the world to uncover the aliens' invasion plans, and hopefully stop them.However, an even bigger threat to XCOM 2 than aliens are its performance issues. You can expect dodgy console ports to run like bloated dogs but not PC exclusives! Firaxis says they are committed to fixing things, which is nice, but until that happens it's a case of buyer beware.Thankfully the game is stellar despite the performance issues. It's notoriously difficult, so f you're not the kind for careful planning, the difficulty of XCOM will wear you down quite quickly. However, if you've got the time and inclination to really sink your teeth into a real challenge - and can get past the performance issues - there's really nothing else out there like it.https://youtu.be/6UWh6FgA7ko"
