76561198066597202,Recommended,268500,21286968,"Posted: 17 February, 2016",all,SpockEndil,"Very short review, just to post my positive recommendation.The game is better on almost all dimensions than its predecessor, which itself was one of the best games in recent years.  The graphics and sound are better, the strategic gameplay is better, and the tactical (battlefield) gameplay is at least as good; maybe better.The ability to mod the game seems pretty much limitless.  I made numerous small changes to enhance my immersion in the game just by editing the .ini files using a text editor.  I even created two entirely new, custom classes for myself by making simple .ini changes (because every game where humans face off against aliens with impossible odds should have a Master Chief and a Shepard).  I can only imagine what will be made available in a few months by talented designers using the game's construction kit.A couple of miscellaneous comments regarding frequently posted complaints:The mission timers that have created a sharp division of opinion generally haven't been a problem.  Overall they probably rate a slight negative because they're overused (individual experience may vary, based on random mission generation), although they create a welcome strategic challenge on the occasions when they make sense (e.g., stop aliens from blowing something up).I've seen frequent complaints that the game is too difficult.  I don't think that's accurate.  The game does, however, require somewhat different tactical approaches than the previous game.  The previous tactic of moving a few steps, setting overwatch, and baiting the enemy into moving into your killzone won't work on the timed missions.  On the other hand, the various types of soldiers now have powerful strategic synergies which I was only beginning to understand by the time I finished the game.  I look forward to building my characters on the next play through in a manner to take advantage of some of those strategies.Finally, some people do seem to have encountered genuine technical problems, but I experienced very few glitches; none of which persisted after a save and reload.I loved the final mission for multiple reasons, none of which I can mention without creating a spoiler.  It both leaves me wanting to start another play through (which I'm going to do right now), and excited for XCom 3.Edited to add:I really hate the stupid Steam-reported time played.  It only counts time played while on-line, which I usually am not.  I've played more than the 1.6 hours shown, or whatever it is now.  I started it four times, three of which I re-started after learning cool new things about the way the game worked, and one of which I finished after deciding that I had learned the game well enough to actually play it."
