76561198029699689,Recommended,268500,24547528,"Posted: 26 July, 2016",all,Ketterking,"This is one of my top 5 games of all time!If you played EU/EW you have a very small idea of what the game is going to be like. I have a bit of time logged into those and thought I knew exactly what Xcom 2 was going to be like when it came out. Yes, you still move your soldiers from cover to cover and throw round after round at a superior alien race, but the whole atmosphere is different as you try and liberate a conquered and blinded planet. You most definitely are conquered. Fighting against superior weaponry and quite an advanced opponent, the game is a struggle, even in the latter stages. Cringing as you miss a 90% shot from 4 tiles away and cheering as you land a mile long snipe on a 13% shot through a car.Xcom 2 used to suffer from a lot of bugs and unoptimized related issues but the Dev team has been incredibly diligent at ironing out the game into the master piece that is truly is. Along with releasing DLC that is just more epic each time you play. You know full well what you are getting when one comes out, they explain very thoroughly what is in each bundle and show case it in many pictures. So, don't be deceived by the nay-sayers.Even if you don't like buying DLC, this game has such a great community that you don't have to spend an extra cent to get many more hours of enjoyment per mod. Long War is even releasing quite large mods which alter the game a surprising amount while remaining true to the basics of the game. I personally play with them all on after having played through Vanilla.Pros;- The vast amount of customization options with mods, dlc, and just the basic character customization tools.- Destructible terrain- The community with all its imagination.- Continuing release of stellar content.Cons;- The massive framerate and lag issues on release (Which have since been fixed to an unnoticible thing of the past)- Lack of an official Alien DLC with a handful of new aliens (Just would personally like to see some since there are a few missing from EU/EW)TL;DR  This is a great game, give it a try and look at the workshop for variety. Carefully look at the DLC which is fairly priced in my opinion as it describes exactly what you get, contrary to many gripes. Different atmosphere from previous titles and continuing to get even more fun as they release more content. Any issues with the game have been ironed out or are easily fixed with a little patience and a well-mannered note to the Dev team! 10/10Welcome back, Commander!"
