76561198125153840,Recommended,268500,25127940,"Posted: 25 August, 2016",all,Killerkitty641,"This is a fantasitc game. No longer are you the best-and-brightest of humanity, battaling it out with the aliens wherever you find them. You are hunted by a alein-controled overlord system known as ADVENT. You have to strike from the shadows and prevent them from reaching their ultimate goal... It is a very difficult game compared to EU, and in a different way to UFO Defense. In UFO Defense, you loose lots of soldiers early on because the aliens are so advanced. In Xcom 2, the loss of a single soldier in your 4-person (6 with upgrades) squad is felt more keenly, because they are experienced and if you fail the mission and leave the body behind, you loose all the gear from that soldier.Also, lots of people have been complaining about bugs. I have only experienced a few minor bugs, such as position locks for soldiers (entirely visual, doesn't affect gameplay) and 1 positioning/ line of sight bug, where some ADVENT in a building saw my sniper through a floor and went up to kill him (he survived). That was the only time. The ""position lock"" was when a viper tounge-grabbed my specialist behiind a car that was on fire. When it exploded, it killed the viper and injured my soldier, leaving them in the lock position.Also, loads of great mods. They can really improve the experience, especially Long War's alien addon pack (adds more aliens)."
